0:0:0,131 --> 0:0:7,33
[Intro music]
(Vote 2012)


2
0:0:7,33 --> 0:0:9,229
(Vice Presidential Debate)


3
0:0:9,229 --> 0:0:11,454
(PBS NewsHour)


4
0:0:11,454 --> 0:0:17,367
[Off voice] Welcome to the PBS NewsHour special coverage of the 2012 vice presidential debate


5
0:0:17,367 --> 0:0:22,372
between Vice President Joe Biden and Congressman Paul Ryan of Wisconsin.


6
0:0:22,372 --> 0:0:24,5
[Judy Woodruff] Good evening, I'm Judy Woodruff


7
0:0:24,5 --> 0:0:29,818
[Gwen Ifill] And I'm Gwen Ifill. Tonight will be  the only debate between the vice presidential candidates.


8
0:0:29,818 --> 0:0:34,407
It will be moderated by Martha Raddatz of ABC News, and it starts in less than a minute


9
0:0:34,407 --> 0:0:38,494
from the Norton Center on the campus of Centre College in Danville, Kentucky.


10
0:0:38,494 --> 0:0:42,78
[Judy Woodruff] Mark Shields and David Brooks are here with us and after the debate,


11
0:0:42,78 --> 0:0:48,726
we will talk to NewsHour political editor Christina Bellantoni, to presidential historian Michael Beschloss,


12
0:0:48,726 --> 0:0:55,224
plus Jonathan Martin of Politico and Sam Youngman of Reuters will all join us from the debate site.


13
0:0:55,224 --> 0:1:1,547
[Gwen Ifill] We'll also be streaming the debate online and offering additional content on our live blog.


14
0:1:1,547 --> 0:1:10,921
[Judy Woodruff] And we're on the edge of our seats and now here's the moderator, Martha Raddatz.


15
0:1:10,921 --> 0:1:12,917
(Live - Norton Center, Centre College)


16
0:1:12,917 --> 0:1:13,848
﻿[Martha Raddatz] Good evening,


17
0:1:13,848 --> 0:1:18,839
and welcome to the  first and only vice presidential debate of 2012,


18
0:1:18,839 --> 0:1:22,24
sponsored by the  Commission on Presidential Debates.


19
0:1:22,24 --> 0:1:26,691
I'm Martha Raddatz of ABC News, and I  am honored to moderate this debate


20
0:1:26,691 --> 0:1:31,439
between 2 men who have dedicated  much of their lives to public service.


21
0:1:31,439 --> 0:1:36,44
Tonight's debate is divided between domestic and foreign policy issues.


22
0:1:36,44 --> 0:1:39,316
And  I'm going to move back and forth between foreign and domestic


23
0:1:39,316 --> 0:1:42,809
since  that is what a vice president or president would have to do.


24
0:1:42,809 --> 0:1:45,275
We will have 9 different segments.


25
0:1:45,275 --> 0:1:49,409
At the beginning of each segment, I will ask both candidates a question,


26
0:1:49,409 --> 0:1:51,84
and they will each have 2 minutes to answer.


27
0:1:51,84 --> 0:1:56,321
Then I will encourage a discussion between the candidates with follow-up questions.


28
0:1:56,321 --> 0:2:0,414
By coin toss, it has been determined that Vice President Biden


29
0:2:0,414 --> 0:2:3,64
will be first to answer the opening question.


30
0:2:3,64 --> 0:2:6,8
We have a wonderful audience here at Centre College tonight.


31
0:2:6,8 --> 0:2:11,168
You will no doubt hear their enthusiasm at the end of the debate and right now


32
0:2:11,168 --> 0:2:29,227
as we welcome Vice President Joe Biden and Congressman Paul Ryan. 
(Applause.)


33
0:2:29,227 --> 0:2:31,335
Very nice to see you. Very nice to see you.


34
0:2:31,335 --> 0:2:41,341
[Joe Biden]: How are you doing?


35
0:2:41,341 --> 0:2:44,22
[Raddatz] OK, you got your little wave to the families in. That's great.


36
0:2:44,22 --> 0:2:48,7
Good evening, gentlemen. It really is an honor to be here with both of you.


37
0:2:48,7 --> 0:2:52,604
I would like to begin with Libya on a rather somber note.


38
0:2:52,604 --> 0:2:56,589
One month ago tonight, on the anniversary of 9/11,


39
0:2:56,589 --> 0:3:0,773
Ambassador Chris Stevens and 3 other brave Americans were killed


40
0:3:0,773 --> 0:3:3,122
in a terrorist attack in Benghazi.


41
0:3:3,122 --> 0:3:7,973
The State Department has now made clear there were no protesters there.


42
0:3:7,973 --> 0:3:11,891
It was a pre-planned assault by heavily armed men.


43
0:3:11,891 --> 0:3:16,706
Wasn't this a massive intelligence failure, Vice President Biden?


44
0:3:16,706 --> 0:3:18,486
[Joe Biden] What it was, it was a tragedy, Martha.


45
0:3:18,486 --> 0:3:23,634
It — Chris Stevens was one of our best. We lost 3 of our other brave Americans.


46
0:3:23,634 --> 0:3:27,886
And I can make absolutely 2 commitments to you and all of the American people tonight:


47
0:3:27,886 --> 0:3:33,802
One, we will find and bring to justice the men who did this.


48
0:3:33,802 --> 0:3:35,853
And secondly, we will get to the bottom of it,


49
0:3:35,853 --> 0:3:38,362
and whatever — wherever the facts lead us,


50
0:3:38,362 --> 0:3:41,829
wherever they lead us, we will make clear to the American public,


51
0:3:41,829 --> 0:3:44,613
because whatever mistakes were made will not be made again.


52
0:3:44,613 --> 0:3:46,659
When you're looking at a president, Martha,


53
0:3:46,659 --> 0:3:50,756
it seems to me that you should take a look at his most important responsibility.


54
0:3:50,756 --> 0:3:54,93
That's carrying forward the national security of the country.


55
0:3:54,93 --> 0:3:57,872
And the best way to do that is take a look at how he's handled he issues of the day.


56
0:3:57,872 --> 0:4:1,69
On Iraq, the president said he would end the war.


57
0:4:1,69 --> 0:4:3,955
Governor Romney said that was a tragic mistake;


58
0:4:3,955 --> 0:4:6,19
we should have left 30 — that he ended it —


59
0:4:6,19 --> 0:4:10,738
Governor Romney said that was a tragic mistake; we should have left 30,000 troops there.


60
0:4:10,738 --> 0:4:14,805
With regard to Afghanistan, he said he will end the war in 2014.


61
0:4:14,805 --> 0:4:17,902
Governor Romney said we should not set a date, number 1,


62
0:4:17,902 --> 0:4:21,59
and number 2, with regard to 2014, it depends.


63
0:4:21,59 --> 0:4:24,738
When it came to Osama bin Laden, the president,


64
0:4:24,738 --> 0:4:28,405
the first day in office — I was sitting with him in the Oval Office.


65
0:4:28,405 --> 0:4:30,815
He called in the CIA and signed an order saying,


66
0:4:30,815 --> 0:4:32,93
my highest priority is to get bin Laden.


67
0:4:32,93 --> 0:4:37,256
Prior to the election, prior to the — him being sworn in,


68
0:4:37,256 --> 0:4:39,876
Governor Romney was asked a question about how he would proceed.


69
0:4:39,876 --> 0:4:42,543
He said, I wouldn't move heaven and earth to get bin Laden.


70
0:4:42,543 --> 0:4:47,66
He didn't understand it was more than about taking a — a murderer off the battlefield;


71
0:4:47,66 --> 0:4:51,543
it was about restoring America's heart and letting terrorists around the world know


72
0:4:51,543 --> 0:4:56,912
if you do harm to America, we will track you to the gates of hell, if need be.


73
0:4:56,912 --> 0:5:0,497
And lastly, the — the president of the United States has —


74
0:5:0,497 --> 0:5:4,568
has led with a steady hand and clear vision.


75
0:5:4,568 --> 0:5:11,122
Governor Romney, the opposite. The last thing we need now is another war.


76
0:5:11,122 --> 0:5:12,681
[Raddatz] Congressman Ryan.


77
0:5:12,681 --> 0:5:17,794
[Paul Ryan]: [Sighs.] We mourn the loss of these 4 Americans who were murdered.


78
0:5:17,794 --> 0:5:20,858
When you take a look at what has happened just in the last few weeks,


79
0:5:20,858 --> 0:5:23,442
they sent the U.N. ambassador out to say


80
0:5:23,442 --> 0:5:26,727
that this was because of a protest and a YouTube video.


81
0:5:26,727 --> 0:5:32,333
It took the president 2 weeks to acknowledge that this was a terrorist attack.


82
0:5:32,333 --> 0:5:35,127
He went to the U.N., and in his speech at the U.N.


83
0:5:35,127 --> 0:5:37,763
he said 5 times — he talked about the YouTube video.


84
0:5:37,763 --> 0:5:44,25
Look, if we are hit by terrorists, we're going to call it for what it is, a terrorist attack.


85
0:5:44,25 --> 0:5:48,717
Our ambassador in Paris has a Marine detachment guarding him.


86
0:5:48,717 --> 0:5:53,245
Shouldn't we have a Marine detachment guarding our ambassador in Benghazi,


87
0:5:53,245 --> 0:5:58,533
a place where we knew that there was an al-Qaida cell with arms?


88
0:5:58,533 --> 0:6:2,399
This is becoming more troubling by the day.


89
0:6:2,399 --> 0:6:3,837
They first blamed the YouTube video;


90
0:6:3,837 --> 0:6:8,164
now they're trying to blame the Romney-Ryan ticket for making this an issue.


91
0:6:8,164 --> 0:6:13,4
And with respect to Iraq, we had the same position before the withdrawal,


92
0:6:13,4 --> 0:6:16,58
which was we agreed with the Obama administration:


93
0:6:16,58 --> 0:6:20,462
Let's have a Status of Forces Agreement to make sure that we secure our gains.


94
0:6:20,462 --> 0:6:24,646
The vice president was put in charge of those negotiations by President Obama,


95
0:6:24,646 --> 0:6:26,7
and they failed to get the agreement.


96
0:6:26,7 --> 0:6:30,58
We don't have a Status of Forces Agreement because they failed to get one.


97
0:6:30,58 --> 0:6:32,5
That's what we are talking about.


98
0:6:32,5 --> 0:6:34,73
And when it comes to our veterans,


99
0:6:34,73 --> 0:6:37,708
we owe them a great debt of gratitude for what they've done for us,


100
0:6:37,708 --> 0:6:40,346
including your son Beau.


101
0:6:40,346 --> 0:6:44,866
But we also want to make sure that we don't lose the things we fought so hard to get.


102
0:6:44,866 --> 0:6:47,225
And with respect to Afghanistan and the 2014 deadline,


103
0:6:47,225 --> 0:6:49,879
we agree with a 2014 transition.


104
0:6:49,879 --> 0:6:53,326
But what we also want to do is make sure that we're not projecting weakness abroad,


105
0:6:53,326 --> 0:6:54,811
and that's what's happening here.


106
0:6:54,811 --> 0:6:59,69
This Benghazi issue would be a tragedy in and of itself.


107
0:6:59,69 --> 0:7:2,721
But unfortunately it's indicative of a broader problem,


108
0:7:2,721 --> 0:7:5,234
and that is what we are watching on our TV screens


109
0:7:5,234 --> 0:7:7,988
is the unraveling of the Obama foreign policy,


110
0:7:7,988 --> 0:7:12,105
which is making the world more — more chaotic and us less safe.


111
0:7:12,105 --> 0:7:15,721
[Raddatz]: I just want to talk to you about right in the middle of the crisis.


112
0:7:15,721 --> 0:7:19,69
Governor Romney — and you're talking about this again tonight —


113
0:7:19,69 --> 0:7:24,819
talked about the weakness, talked about apologies from the Obama administration.


114
0:7:24,819 --> 0:7:28,746
Was that really appropriate right in the middle of the crisis?


115
0:7:28,746 --> 0:7:32,352
[Ryan] On that same day, the Obama administration had the exact same position.


116
0:7:32,352 --> 0:7:35,89
Let's recall that they disavowed their own statement


117
0:7:35,89 --> 0:7:38,52
that they had put out earlier in the day in Cairo.


118
0:7:38,52 --> 0:7:39,929
So we had the same position, but we will —


119
0:7:39,929 --> 0:7:43,131
it's never to early to speak out for our values.


120
0:7:43,131 --> 0:7:47,64
We should have spoken out right away when the Green Revolution was up and starting,


121
0:7:47,64 --> 0:7:50,213
when the mullahs in Iran were attacking their people.


122
0:7:50,213 --> 0:7:52,952
We should not have called Bashar Assad a reformer


123
0:7:52,952 --> 0:7:56,264
when he was turning his Russian-provided guns on his own people.


124
0:7:56,264 --> 0:8:2,64
We should always stand up for peace, for democracy, for individual rights,


125
0:8:2,64 --> 0:8:5,331
and we should not be imposing these devastating defense cuts,


126
0:8:5,331 --> 0:8:9,377
because what that does when we equivocate on our values,


127
0:8:9,377 --> 0:8:11,524
when we show that we're cutting our own defense —
[Biden] Am I going to get to say anything here?


128
0:8:11,524 --> 0:8:12,855
[Ryan] — it makes us more weak.


129
0:8:12,855 --> 0:8:14,955
It projects weakness, and when we look weak,


130
0:8:14,955 --> 0:8:16,994
our adversaries are much more willing to test us,


131
0:8:16,994 --> 0:8:19,298
they're more brazen in their attacks, and our allies are less willing to —


132
0:8:19,298 --> 0:8:22,344
[Biden] With all due respect, that's a bunch of malarkey. In fact —


133
0:8:22,344 --> 0:8:23,767
[Raddatz] And why is that so?


134
0:8:23,767 --> 0:8:26,343
[Biden] Because not a single thing he said is accurate. First of all —


135
0:8:26,343 --> 0:8:27,382
[Raddatz] Be specific.


136
0:8:27,382 --> 0:8:28,651
[Biden] I will be very specific.


137
0:8:28,651 --> 0:8:32,743
Number one, the — this lecture on embassy security —


138
0:8:32,743 --> 0:8:36,82
the congressman here cut embassy security in his budget


139
0:8:36,82 --> 0:8:41,692
by $300 million below what we asked for, number 1.


140
0:8:41,692 --> 0:8:43,564
So much for the embassy security piece.


141
0:8:43,564 --> 0:8:47,123
Number 2, Governor Romney, before he knew the facts,


142
0:8:47,123 --> 0:8:49,905
before he even knew that our ambassador was killed,


143
0:8:49,905 --> 0:8:55,403
he was out making a political statement which was panned by the media around the world.


144
0:8:55,403 --> 0:8:59,68
And this talk about this — this weakness, I —


145
0:8:59,68 --> 0:9:2,136
I don't understand what my friend's talking about here.


146
0:9:2,136 --> 0:9:7,308
We — this is a president who's gone out and done everything he has said he was going to do.


147
0:9:7,308 --> 0:9:11,438
This is the guy who's repaired our alliances so the rest of the world follows us again.


148
0:9:11,438 --> 0:9:15,438
This is the guy who brought the entire world, including Russia and China,


149
0:9:15,438 --> 0:9:20,905
to bring about the most devastating, most devastating


150
0:9:20,905 --> 0:9:27,536
— the most devastating efforts on Iran to make sure that they in fact stop with their —


151
0:9:27,536 --> 0:9:31,455
look, I — I — I just — I mean, these guys bet against America all the time.


152
0:9:31,455 --> 0:9:32,989
[Raddatz] Can we talk about —
[Biden] Yeah, sure.


153
0:9:32,989 --> 0:9:34,843
[Raddatz]  let me go back to Libya.


154
0:9:34,843 --> 0:9:38,143
[Biden] What were you first told about the attack?


155
0:9:38,143 --> 0:9:41,568
Why were people talking about protests?


156
0:9:41,568 --> 0:9:47,637
When people in the consulate first saw armed men attacking with guns,


157
0:9:47,637 --> 0:9:49,822
there were no protesters.
[Biden] Because...


158
0:9:49,822 --> 0:9:52,273
[Raddatz] Why did that go on for weeks?
[Biden] Because that's exactly what we were told —


159
0:9:52,273 --> 0:9:56,236
[Raddatz] By who?
[Biden] — by the intelligence community. The intelligence community told us that.


160
0:9:56,236 --> 0:10:1,351
As they learned more facts about exactly what happened, they changed their assessment.


161
0:10:1,351 --> 0:10:4,587
That's why there's also an investigation headed by Tom Pickering,


162
0:10:4,587 --> 0:10:7,787
a leading diplomat in the — from the Reagan years,


163
0:10:7,787 --> 0:10:10,653
who is doing an investigation as to whether or not there were any lapses,


164
0:10:10,653 --> 0:10:13,541
what the lapses were, so that they will never happen again. But —


165
0:10:13,541 --> 0:10:15,312
[Raddatz]  And they wanted more security there.


166
0:10:15,312 --> 0:10:18,291
[Biden] Well, we weren't told they wanted more security again.


167
0:10:18,291 --> 0:10:20,521
We did not know they wanted more security again.


168
0:10:20,521 --> 0:10:24,328
And by the way, at the time we were told exactly —


169
0:10:24,328 --> 0:10:28,876
we said exactly what the intelligence community told us that they knew.


170
0:10:28,876 --> 0:10:30,53
That was the assessment.


171
0:10:30,53 --> 0:10:32,733
And as the intelligence community changed their view,


172
0:10:32,733 --> 0:10:34,912
we made it clear they changed their view.


173
0:10:34,912 --> 0:10:37,589
That's why I said, we will get to the bottom of this.


174
0:10:37,589 --> 0:10:39,979
You know, usually when there's a crisis, we pull together.


175
0:10:39,979 --> 0:10:42,2
We pull together as a nation.


176
0:10:42,2 --> 0:10:45,226
But as I said, even before we knew what happened to the ambassador,


177
0:10:45,226 --> 0:10:48,876
the Governor was holding a press conference — was holding a press conference.


178
0:10:48,876 --> 0:10:50,868
That's not presidential leadership.


179
0:10:50,868 --> 0:10:53,61
[Raddatz] Mr. Ryan, I want to ask you about —


180
0:10:53,61 --> 0:10:56,62
the Romney campaign talks a lot about no apologies.


181
0:10:56,62 --> 0:10:58,797
He has a book called No Apologies.


182
0:10:58,797 --> 0:11:3,94
Should the U.S. have apologized for Americans burning Qurans in Afghanistan?


183
0:11:3,94 --> 0:11:9,195
Should the U.S. apologize for U.S. Marines urinating on Taliban corpses?


184
0:11:9,195 --> 0:11:14,343
[Ryan] Oh, gosh, yes. Urinating on Taliban corpses? What we should not apologize for —


185
0:11:14,343 --> 0:11:15,751
[Raddatz] Burning Qurans immediately.


186
0:11:15,751 --> 0:11:19,55
[Ryan] What — what we should not be apologizing for are standing up for our values.


187
0:11:19,55 --> 0:11:22,471
What we should not be doing is saying to the Egyptian people,


188
0:11:22,471 --> 0:11:25,706
while Mubarak is cracking down on them,


189
0:11:25,706 --> 0:11:28,327
that he's a good guy and then the next week say he ought to go.


190
0:11:28,327 --> 0:11:31,758
What we should not be doing is rejecting claims for


191
0:11:31,758 --> 0:11:35,527
— calls for more security in our barracks, in our Marine —


192
0:11:35,527 --> 0:11:38,25
we need Marines in Benghazi


193
0:11:38,25 --> 0:11:41,573
when the commander on the ground says we need more forces for security.


194
0:11:41,573 --> 0:11:44,675
There were requests for extra security. Those requests were not honored.


195
0:11:44,675 --> 0:11:48,321
Look, this was the anniversary of 9/11.


196
0:11:48,321 --> 0:11:53,188
It was Libya, a country we knew we had al-Qaida cells there.


197
0:11:53,188 --> 0:11:56,783
As we know, al-Qaida and its affiliates are on the rise in Northern Africa.


198
0:11:56,783 --> 0:12:2,75
And we did not give our ambassador in Benghazi a Marine detachment?


199
0:12:2,75 --> 0:12:5,921
Of course there is an investigation so we can make sure that this never happens again.


200
0:12:5,921 --> 0:12:10,358
But when it comes to speaking up for our values, we should not apologize for those.


201
0:12:10,358 --> 0:12:11,75
Here is the problem.


202
0:12:11,75 --> 0:12:15,609
Look at all the various issues out there and that's unraveling before our eyes.


203
0:12:15,609 --> 0:12:17,911
The vice president talks about sanctions on Iran.


204
0:12:17,911 --> 0:12:19,211
They got — we've had 4 —


205
0:12:19,211 --> 0:12:20,388
[Raddatz]  Let's move to Iran.


206
0:12:20,388 --> 0:12:24,148
I'd actually like to move to Iran because there is really no bigger national security —


207
0:12:24,148 --> 0:12:25,394
[Ryan] Absolutely.


208
0:12:25,394 --> 0:12:26,878
[Raddatz] — this country is facing.


209
0:12:26,878 --> 0:12:29,342
Both President Obama and Governor Romney have said


210
0:12:29,342 --> 0:12:35,362
they will prevent Iran from getting a nuclear weapon, even if that means military action.


211
0:12:35,362 --> 0:12:38,314
Last week former Defense Secretary Bob Gates said


212
0:12:38,314 --> 0:12:41,328
a strike on Iran's facilities would not work and,


213
0:12:41,328 --> 0:12:46,8
quote, could prove catastrophic, haunting us for generations.


214
0:12:46,8 --> 0:12:51,756
Can the 2 of you be absolutely clear and specific to the American people


215
0:12:51,756 --> 0:12:56,151
how effective would a military strike be? Congressman Ryan.


216
0:12:56,151 --> 0:13:0,404
[Ryan] We cannot allow Iran to gain a nuclear weapons capability.


217
0:13:0,404 --> 0:13:4,736
Now, let's take a look at where we've gone — come from.


218
0:13:4,736 --> 0:13:6,144
When Barack Obama was elected,


219
0:13:6,144 --> 0:13:10,271
they had enough fissile material, nuclear material, to make 1 bomb.


220
0:13:10,271 --> 0:13:11,776
Now they have enough for 5.


221
0:13:11,776 --> 0:13:13,199
They're racing toward a nuclear weapon.


222
0:13:13,199 --> 0:13:16,7
They're 4 years closer toward a nuclear weapons capability.


223
0:13:16,7 --> 0:13:18,297
We've had 4 different sanctions at the U.N. on Iran,


224
0:13:18,297 --> 0:13:21,235
3 from the Bush administration, 1 here.


225
0:13:21,235 --> 0:13:23,91
And the only reason we got it is because Russia watered it down


226
0:13:23,91 --> 0:13:27,81
and prevented the — the sanctions from hitting the central bank.


227
0:13:27,81 --> 0:13:30,115
Mitt Romney proposed these sanctions in 2007.


228
0:13:30,115 --> 0:13:33,6
In Congress, I've been fighting for these sanctions since 2009.


229
0:13:33,6 --> 0:13:35,597
The administration was blocking us every step of the way.


230
0:13:35,597 --> 0:13:39,47
Only because we had strong bipartisan support for these tough sanctions


231
0:13:39,47 --> 0:13:43,981
were we able to overrule their objections and put them in spite of the administration.


232
0:13:43,981 --> 0:13:47,225
Imagine what would have happened if we had these sanctions in place earlier.


233
0:13:47,225 --> 0:13:50,517
You think Iran's not brazen? Look at what they're doing.


234
0:13:50,517 --> 0:13:52,971
They're stepping up their terrorist attacks.


235
0:13:52,971 --> 0:13:55,108
They tried a terrorist attack in the United States last year


236
0:13:55,108 --> 0:13:59,74
when they tried to blow up the Saudi ambassador at a restaurant in Washington, D.C.


237
0:13:59,74 --> 0:14:1,194
And talk about credibility.


238
0:14:1,194 --> 0:14:4,642
When this administration says that all options are on the table,


239
0:14:4,642 --> 0:14:8,922
they send out senior administration officials that send all these mixed signals.


240
0:14:8,922 --> 0:14:13,17
And so in order solve this peacefully, which is everybody's goal,


241
0:14:13,17 --> 0:14:16,815
you have to have the ayatollahs change their minds.


242
0:14:16,815 --> 0:14:20,469
Look at where they are. They're moving faster toward a nuclear weapon.


243
0:14:20,469 --> 0:14:23,508
It's because this administration has no credibility on this issue.


244
0:14:23,508 --> 0:14:27,861
It's because this administration watered down sanctions, delayed sanctions,


245
0:14:27,861 --> 0:14:29,38
tried to stop us from putting the tough sanctions in place.


246
0:14:29,38 --> 0:14:31,173
Now we have them in place because of Congress.


247
0:14:31,173 --> 0:14:35,356
They say the military option's on the table but it's not being viewed as credible,


248
0:14:35,356 --> 0:14:40,483
and the key is to do this peacefully, is to make sure that we have credibility.


249
0:14:40,483 --> 0:14:44,64
Under a Romney administration, we will have credibility on this issue.


250
0:14:44,64 --> 0:14:45,795
[Raddatz]  Vice President Biden.


251
0:14:45,795 --> 0:14:46,941
[Biden] It's incredible. (Chuckles.)


252
0:14:46,941 --> 0:14:52,862
Look, imagine had we let the Republican Congress work out the sanctions.


253
0:14:52,862 --> 0:14:57,576
You think there's any possibility the entire world would have joined us,


254
0:14:57,576 --> 0:15:0,841
Russia and China, all of our allies?


255
0:15:0,841 --> 0:15:6,393
These are the most crippling sanctions in the history of sanctions, period, period.


256
0:15:6,393 --> 0:15:10,607
When Governor Romney's asked about it, he said, we got to keep these sanctions.


257
0:15:10,607 --> 0:15:12,599
When you say, well, you're talking about doing more,


258
0:15:12,599 --> 0:15:14,276
what are you — are you — you're going to go to war? Is that you want to do now?


259
0:15:14,276 --> 0:15:15,983
[Ryan]  We want to prevent war!


260
0:15:15,983 --> 0:15:18,89
[Biden]  We have — and I — the interesting thing is, how they're going to prevent war.


261
0:15:18,89 --> 0:15:22,29
How are they going to prevent war if they say that there's nothing more that we


262
0:15:22,29 --> 0:15:26,55
— that they say we should do than what we've already done, number 1?


263
0:15:26,55 --> 0:15:31,539
And number 2, with regard to the ability of the United States to take action militarily,


264
0:15:31,539 --> 0:15:36,123
it is — it is not in my purview to talk about classified information.


265
0:15:36,123 --> 0:15:41,827
But we feel quite confident we could deal a serious blow to the Iranians.


266
0:15:41,827 --> 0:15:46,131
But number 2, the Iranians are — the Israelis and the United States —


267
0:15:46,131 --> 0:15:50,697
our military and intelligence communities are absolutely the same exact place


268
0:15:50,697 --> 0:15:57,14
in terms of how close — how close the Iranians are to getting a nuclear weapon.


269
0:15:57,14 --> 0:15:59,261
They are a good way away.


270
0:15:59,261 --> 0:16:2,946
There is no difference between our view and theirs.


271
0:16:2,946 --> 0:16:5,323
When my friend talks about fissile material,


272
0:16:5,323 --> 0:16:10,62
they have to take this highly enriched uranium, get it from 20% up.


273
0:16:10,62 --> 0:16:13,548
Then they have to be able to have something to put it in.


274
0:16:13,548 --> 0:16:17,573
There is no weapon that the Iranians have at this point.


275
0:16:17,573 --> 0:16:22,843
Both the Israelis and we know we'll know if they start the process of building a weapon.


276
0:16:22,843 --> 0:16:29,34
So all this bluster I keep hearing, all this loose talk — what are they talking about?


277
0:16:29,34 --> 0:16:31,75
Are you talking about to be more credible?


278
0:16:31,75 --> 0:16:33,25
But what — what more can the president do?


279
0:16:33,25 --> 0:16:35,85
Stand before the United Nations, tell the whole world,


280
0:16:35,85 --> 0:16:37,963
directly communicate to the ayatollah:


281
0:16:37,963 --> 0:16:43,112
We will not let them acquire a nuclear weapon, period,


282
0:16:43,112 --> 0:16:44,967
unless he's talking about going to war.


283
0:16:44,967 --> 0:16:46,535
[Ryan]  Martha, let's just —


284
0:16:46,535 --> 0:16:47,635
[Raddatz] Congressman Ryan.


285
0:16:47,635 --> 0:16:51,773
[Ryan]  — let's look at this from the view of the ayatollahs. What do they see?


286
0:16:51,773 --> 0:16:56,792
They see this administration trying to water down sanctions in Congress for over 2 years.


287
0:16:56,792 --> 0:16:59,613
They're moving faster toward a nuclear weapon;


288
0:16:59,613 --> 0:17:1,76
they're spinning the centrifuges faster.


289
0:17:1,76 --> 0:17:4,733
They see us saying, when we come into the administration,


290
0:17:4,733 --> 0:17:8,314
when they're sworn in, we need more space with our ally Israel.


291
0:17:8,314 --> 0:17:13,371
They see President Obama in New York City the same day Bibi Netanyahu is,


292
0:17:13,371 --> 0:17:16,984
and he's — instead of meeting with him goes on a — on a daily talk show.


293
0:17:16,984 --> 0:17:21,45
They see — when we say that these options are on the table,


294
0:17:21,45 --> 0:17:24,165
the Secretary of defense walked them back.


295
0:17:24,165 --> 0:17:26,906
They are not changing their mind.


296
0:17:26,906 --> 0:17:29,592
That's what we have to do, is change their mind


297
0:17:29,592 --> 0:17:31,587
so they stop pursuing nuclear weapons, and they're going faster.


298
0:17:31,587 --> 0:17:32,81
[Raddatz] How will you do it so quickly?


299
0:17:32,81 --> 0:17:37,938
Look, you both saw Benjamin Netanyahu hold up that picture of a bomb


300
0:17:37,938 --> 0:17:42,621
with the red line and talking about the red line being in spring.


301
0:17:42,621 --> 0:17:48,274
So can you solve this — if the Romney-Ryan ticket is elected,


302
0:17:48,274 --> 0:17:54,29
can you solve this in 2 months before spring and avoid nuclear — nuclear --


303
0:17:54,29 --> 0:17:55,364
[Ryan] We — we can debate a timeline.


304
0:17:55,364 --> 0:17:56,49
[Raddatz] (Inaudible.)


305
0:17:56,49 --> 0:17:56,934
[Ryan] We can debate the timeline,


306
0:17:56,934 --> 0:17:58,541
whether there's — it's that short a time or longer.


307
0:17:58,541 --> 0:18:0,748
I — I agree that it's probably longer.


308
0:18:0,748 --> 0:18:3,456
Number 2, it's all about credibility.


309
0:18:3,456 --> 0:18:4,356
[Raddatz] You don't agree with that bomb and what the Israelis —


310
0:18:4,356 --> 0:18:5,161
[Biden] No, look — (inaudible) —


311
0:18:5,161 --> 0:18:6,261
[Ryan] (Inaudible) — look, we — we both agree —


312
0:18:6,261 --> 0:18:7,484
[Raddatz] Vice President Biden.


313
0:18:7,484 --> 0:18:8,784
[Ryan I don't want to go into classified stuff,


314
0:18:8,784 --> 0:18:12,351
but we both agree that to do this peacefully,


315
0:18:12,351 --> 0:18:14,181
you've got to get them to change their minds.


316
0:18:14,181 --> 0:18:16,98
They're not changing their minds, and look at what this administration does —


317
0:18:16,98 --> 0:18:18,19
[Raddatz] But what do you do — (inaudible) —


318
0:18:18,19 --> 0:18:19,396
[Biden] Let me tell you what the ayatollah sees.


319
0:18:19,396 --> 0:18:19,896
[Ryan] You have to have credibility.


320
0:18:19,896 --> 0:18:21,972
[Biden] The ayatollah sees his economy being crippled.


321
0:18:21,972 --> 0:18:27,898
The ayatollah sees that there are 50% fewer exports of oil.


322
0:18:27,898 --> 0:18:30,941
He sees the currency going into the tank.


323
0:18:30,941 --> 0:18:33,564
He sees the economy going into free fall,


324
0:18:33,564 --> 0:18:36,465
and he sees the world for the first time totally united


325
0:18:36,465 --> 0:18:39,598
in opposition to him getting a nuclear weapon.


326
0:18:39,598 --> 0:18:42,674
Now, with regard to Bibi, he's been my friend for 39 years.


327
0:18:42,674 --> 0:18:45,395
The president has met with Bibi a dozen times.


328
0:18:45,395 --> 0:18:48,666
He's spoken to Bibi Netanyahu as much as he's spoken to anybody.


329
0:18:48,666 --> 0:18:52,688
The idea that we're not — I was in a — just before he went to the U.N.,


330
0:18:52,688 --> 0:18:55,478
I was in a conference call with the — with the president,


331
0:18:55,478 --> 0:18:58,762
with him talking to Bibi, for well over an hour


332
0:18:58,762 --> 0:19:3,496
in — in — in — in — in stark relief and detail about what was going on.


333
0:19:3,496 --> 0:19:5,869
This is a bunch of stuff. Look, here's the deal —


334
0:19:5,869 --> 0:19:7,369
[Raddatz] What does that mean, "a bunch of stuff"?


335
0:19:7,369 --> 0:19:8,823
[Biden] Well, it means it's simply inaccurate.


336
0:19:8,823 --> 0:19:9,708
[Ryan] It's Irish. (Chuckles.)


337
0:19:9,708 --> 0:19:13,61
[Biden] It is. (Laughter.) The Irish call it malarkey.


338
0:19:13,61 --> 0:19:14,91
[Raddatz] Thanks for the translation. OK.


339
0:19:14,91 --> 0:19:15,453
[Biden] No, the Irish call it malarkey. (Laughter.)


340
0:19:15,453 --> 0:19:20,29
But last thing: the secretary of defense has made it absolutely clear.


341
0:19:20,29 --> 0:19:20,837
He didn't walk anything back.


342
0:19:20,837 --> 0:19:26,31
We will not allow the Iranians to get a nuclear weapon.


343
0:19:26,31 --> 0:19:29,469
What Bibi held up there was when they get to the point


344
0:19:29,469 --> 0:19:33,696
where they can enrich uranium enough to put into a weapon,


345
0:19:33,696 --> 0:19:36,684
they don't have a weapon to put it into.


346
0:19:36,684 --> 0:19:39,39
Let's all calm down a little bit here.


347
0:19:39,39 --> 0:19:42,853
Iran is more isolated today than when we took office.


348
0:19:42,853 --> 0:19:47,499
It was on the ascendancy when we took office. It is totally isolated.


349
0:19:47,499 --> 0:19:48,337
[Raddatz] Congressman Ryan —


350
0:19:48,337 --> 0:19:49,56
[Biden] I don't know what world you guys are in.


351
0:19:49,56 --> 0:19:50,6
[Raddatz] Congressman Ryan —


352
0:19:50,6 --> 0:19:51,76
[Ryan] Thank — thank heavens we have these sanctions in place.


353
0:19:51,76 --> 0:19:53,291
It's in spite of their opposition.


354
0:19:53,291 --> 0:19:54,53
[Biden] (Chuckles.) Oh, God.


355
0:19:54,53 --> 0:19:56,76
[Ryan] They have given 20 waivers to this sanction.


356
0:19:56,76 --> 0:19:59,473
And all I have to point to are the results.


357
0:19:59,473 --> 0:20:2,222
They're 4 years closer toward a nuclear weapon.


358
0:20:2,222 --> 0:20:3,87
I think that case speaks for itself.


359
0:20:3,87 --> 0:20:5,385
[Raddatz] Can you tell the American people what's worse than —


360
0:20:5,385 --> 0:20:6,562
[Biden] By the way, they're — no,


361
0:20:6,562 --> 0:20:7,62
no, they are not 4 years closer to a nuclear weapon.


362
0:20:7,62 --> 0:20:8,885
[Raddatz] — another war in the Middle East or —


363
0:20:8,885 --> 0:20:12,936
[Biden] They're — they're closer to being able to get enough fissile material


364
0:20:12,936 --> 0:20:15,793
to put in a weapon if they had a weapon. But —


365
0:20:15,793 --> 0:20:17,293
[Raddatz] You're acting a little bit like they don't want one, though.


366
0:20:17,293 --> 0:20:20,74
[Biden] Oh, I didn't say — no, I'm not saying that's - facts matter, Martha.


367
0:20:20,74 --> 0:20:23,793
You're a foreign policy expert. Facts matter.


368
0:20:23,793 --> 0:20:25,813
All this loose talk about them


369
0:20:25,813 --> 0:20:29,57
— all they have to do is get to — enrich uranium in a certain amount


370
0:20:29,57 --> 0:20:32,833
and they have a weapon — not true. Not true.


371
0:20:32,833 --> 0:20:38,121
They are more — and if we ever have to take action, unlike where we took office,


372
0:20:38,121 --> 0:20:43,416
we will have the world behind us, and that matters. That matters.


373
0:20:43,416 --> 0:20:47,214
[Raddatz] What about Bob Gates' statement? Let me read that again:


374
0:20:47,214 --> 0:20:51,64
"... could prove catastrophic, haunting us for generations."


375
0:20:51,64 --> 0:20:54,27
[Biden] He is right. It could prove catastrophic


376
0:20:54,27 --> 0:20:55,158
if we do — we do it with — (inaudible) —


377
0:20:55,158 --> 0:20:55,966
[Raddatz] Congressman Ryan?


378
0:20:55,966 --> 0:20:58,386
[Ryan] And what it does is it — and it undermines our credibility


379
0:20:58,386 --> 0:21:2,903
by backing up the point when we make it that all options are on the table.


380
0:21:2,903 --> 0:21:3,91
That's the point.


381
0:21:3,91 --> 0:21:6,247
The ayatollahs see these kinds of statements,


382
0:21:6,247 --> 0:21:9,112
and they think, I'm going to get a nuclear weapon.


383
0:21:9,112 --> 0:21:13,795
When — when we see the kind of equivocation that took place


384
0:21:13,795 --> 0:21:17,852
because this administration wanted a precondition policy —


385
0:21:17,852 --> 0:21:21,182
so when the Green Revolution started up, they were silent for 9 days.


386
0:21:21,182 --> 0:21:25,167
When they see us putting des... desperate -  when they see us putting daylight


387
0:21:25,167 --> 0:21:30,156
between ourselves and our allies in Israel, that gives them encouragement.


388
0:21:30,156 --> 0:21:34,191
When they see Russia watering down any further sanctions


389
0:21:34,191 --> 0:21:37,395
— and the only reason we got a U.N. sanction is because Russia watered it down


390
0:21:37,395 --> 0:21:39,834
and prevented these sanctions from being sanctions in the first place.


391
0:21:39,834 --> 0:21:44,676
So when they see this kind of activity, they are encouraged to continue,


392
0:21:44,676 --> 0:21:45,607
and that's the problem.


393
0:21:45,607 --> 0:21:46,353
[Biden] Martha, let me tell you what Russia's — (inaudible) —


394
0:21:46,353 --> 0:21:47,468
[Raddatz] What — let me ask you what's worse:


395
0:21:47,468 --> 0:21:52,13
war in the Middle East, another war in the Middle East, or a nuclear-armed Iran?


396
0:21:52,13 --> 0:21:52,821
[Ryan] I'll tell you what's worse - I'll tell you what's worse.


397
0:21:52,821 --> 0:21:53,321
[Raddatz] Quickly.


398
0:21:53,321 --> 0:21:55,5
[Ryan] A nuclear-armed Iran,


399
0:21:55,5 --> 0:21:57,988
which triggers a nuclear arms race in the Middle East.


400
0:21:57,988 --> 0:22:0,938
This is the world's largest sponsor of — of terrorism.


401
0:22:0,938 --> 0:22:1,792
They've dedicated themselves —


402
0:22:1,792 --> 0:22:2,63
[Biden] That's the only thing my —


403
0:22:2,63 --> 0:22:3,884
[Ryan] — to wiping an entire country off the map.


404
0:22:3,884 --> 0:22:5,43
They call us the Great Satan.


405
0:22:5,43 --> 0:22:7,507
And if they get nuclear weapons,


406
0:22:7,507 --> 0:22:10,313
other people in the neighborhood will pursue their nuclear weapons as well.


407
0:22:10,313 --> 0:22:11,458
[Raddatz] Vice President Biden.


408
0:22:11,458 --> 0:22:12,312
[Ryan] We can't live with that.


409
0:22:12,312 --> 0:22:17,509
[Biden] War should always be the absolute last resort.


410
0:22:17,509 --> 0:22:20,41
That's why these crippling sanctions,


411
0:22:20,41 --> 0:22:22,743
which Bibi Netanyahu says we should continue


412
0:22:22,743 --> 0:22:27,748
— which, if I'm not mistaken, Governor Romney says we — we should continue.


413
0:22:27,748 --> 0:22:31,565
If I — I may be mistaken; he changes his mind so often, I could be wrong.


414
0:22:31,565 --> 0:22:35,35
But the fact of the matter is, he says they're working.


415
0:22:35,35 --> 0:22:39,12
And the fact is that they are being crippled by them.


416
0:22:39,12 --> 0:22:42,559
And we've made it clear, big nations can't bluff.


417
0:22:42,559 --> 0:22:44,847
This president doesn't bluff.


418
0:22:44,847 --> 0:22:46,809
[Raddatz] Gentlemen, I want to bring the conversation


419
0:22:46,809 --> 0:22:50,469
to a different kind of national security issue, the state of our economy.


420
0:22:50,469 --> 0:22:54,5
The number 1 issue here at home is jobs.


421
0:22:54,5 --> 0:22:58,403
The percentage of unemployed just fell below 8%


422
0:22:58,403 --> 0:23:1,487
for the first time in 43 months.


423
0:23:1,487 --> 0:23:6,4
The Obama administration had projected that it would fall below 6% now,


424
0:23:6,4 --> 0:23:10,372
after the addition of close to a trillion dollars in stimulus money.


425
0:23:10,372 --> 0:23:13,291
So will both of you level with the American people?


426
0:23:13,291 --> 0:23:18,267
Can you get unemployment to under 6%, and how long will it take?


427
0:23:18,267 --> 0:23:19,536
[Biden] I don't know how long it will takw


428
0:23:19,536 --> 0:23:20,98
[Raddatz] Vice President Biden.


429
0:23:20,98 --> 0:23:22,0
[Biden] We can and we will get it under 6%.


430
0:23:22,0 --> 0:23:24,526
Let's look at the — let's take a look at the facts.


431
0:23:24,526 --> 0:23:27,687
Let's look at where we were when we came to office.


432
0:23:27,687 --> 0:23:29,757
The economy was in free fall.


433
0:23:29,757 --> 0:23:32,638
We had — the Great Recession hit.


434
0:23:32,638 --> 0:23:43,252
9 million people lost their job, 1.7 — $1.6 trillion in wealth lost in equity in your homes, in retirement accounts from the middle class.


435
0:23:43,252 --> 0:23:45,328
We knew we had to act for the middle class.


436
0:23:45,328 --> 0:23:48,4
We immediately went out and rescued General Motors.


437
0:23:48,4 --> 0:23:51,418
We went ahead and made sure that we cut taxes for the middle class.


438
0:23:51,418 --> 0:23:54,601
And in addition to that, when that — and when that occurred,


439
0:23:54,601 --> 0:23:58,37
what did Romney do? Romney said, no, let Detroit go bankrupt.


440
0:23:58,37 --> 0:24:1,108
We moved in and helped people refinance their homes.


441
0:24:1,108 --> 0:24:4,212
Governor Romney said, no, let foreclosures hit the bottom.


442
0:24:4,212 --> 0:24:6,748
But it shouldn't be surprising for a guy who says


443
0:24:6,748 --> 0:24:8,9
47% of the American people


444
0:24:8,9 --> 0:24:11,733
are unwilling to take responsibility for their own lives.


445
0:24:11,733 --> 0:24:13,933
My friend recently, in a speech in Washington,


446
0:24:13,933 --> 0:24:16,4
said 30% of the American people are takers.


447
0:24:16,4 --> 0:24:21,132
These people are my mom and dad, the people I grew up with, my neighbors.


448
0:24:21,132 --> 0:24:25,452
They pay more effective tax than Governor Romney pays in his federal income tax.


449
0:24:25,452 --> 0:24:28,653
They are elderly people who in fact are living off of Social Security.


450
0:24:28,653 --> 0:24:32,388
They are veterans and people fighting in Afghanistan right now who are,


451
0:24:32,388 --> 0:24:34,211
quote, not paying any taxes.


452
0:24:34,211 --> 0:24:38,2
I've had it up to here with this notion that 47%


453
0:24:38,2 --> 0:24:41,253
— it's about time they take some responsibility here.


454
0:24:41,253 --> 0:24:43,999
And instead of signing pledges to Grover Norquist


455
0:24:43,999 --> 0:24:48,626
not to ask the wealthiest among us to contribute to bring back the middle class,


456
0:24:48,626 --> 0:24:51,536
they should be signing a pledge saying to the middle class,


457
0:24:51,536 --> 0:24:53,159
we're going to level the playing field.


458
0:24:53,159 --> 0:24:55,183
We're going to give you a fair shot again.


459
0:24:55,183 --> 0:24:59,79
We are going to not repeat the mistakes we made in the past


