0:25:3,338 --> 0:25:7,819
making sure that we continue to hemorrhage these tax cuts for the superwealthy.


462
0:25:7,819 --> 0:25:10,33
They're pushing the continuation of a tax cut


463
0:25:10,33 --> 0:25:17,807
that will give an additional $500 billion in tax cuts to 120,000 families.


464
0:25:17,807 --> 0:25:22,123
And they're holding hostage the middle-class tax cut because they say,


465
0:25:22,123 --> 0:25:25,265
we won't pass — we won't continue the middle-class tax cut


466
0:25:25,265 --> 0:25:28,246
unless you give the tax cut for the superwealthy.


467
0:25:28,246 --> 0:25:31,69
It's about time they take some responsibility.


468
0:25:31,69 --> 0:25:31,954
[Raddatz] Mr. Ryan.


469
0:25:31,954 --> 0:25:34,432
[Ryan] Joe and I are from similar towns.


470
0:25:34,432 --> 0:25:36,24
He's from Scranton, Pennsylvania.


471
0:25:36,24 --> 0:25:37,355
I'm from Janesville, Wisconsin.


472
0:25:37,355 --> 0:25:40,214
You know what the unemployment rate in Scranton is today?


473
0:25:40,214 --> 0:25:41,161
[Biden] I sure do.


474
0:25:41,161 --> 0:25:42,199
[Ryan] It's 10%,


475
0:25:42,199 --> 0:25:42,945
[Biden] Yeah.


476
0:25:42,945 --> 0:25:44,168
[Ryan]: You know what it was the day you guys came in?


477
0:25:44,168 --> 0:25:44,822
[Biden] [Inaudible]


478
0:25:44,822 --> 0:25:45,645
[Ryan] 8.5%


479
0:25:45,645 --> 0:25:46,314
[Biden] Yeah.


480
0:25:46,314 --> 0:25:47,845
[Ryan] That's how it's going all around America.


481
0:25:47,845 --> 0:25:48,591
Look —


482
0:25:48,591 --> 0:25:50,771
[Biden] You don't read the statistics. That's not "how it's going."


483
0:25:50,771 --> 0:25:51,794
It's going down.


484
0:25:51,794 --> 0:25:52,833
[Raddatz] (Inaudible) — 2-minute answer, please.


485
0:25:52,833 --> 0:25:58,746
[Ryan] Look — (chuckles) — did they come in and inherit a tough situation? Absolutely.


486
0:25:58,746 --> 0:25:59,815
[Biden] (Chuckles.)


487
0:25:59,815 --> 0:26:1,346
[Ryan] But we're going in the wrong direction!


488
0:26:1,346 --> 0:26:5,435
Look at where we are. The economy is barely limping along.


489
0:26:5,435 --> 0:26:6,935
It's growing at 1.3%.


490
0:26:6,935 --> 0:26:8,589
That's slower than it grew last year,


491
0:26:8,589 --> 0:26:10,658
and last year was slower than the year before.


492
0:26:10,658 --> 0:26:14,4
Job growth in September was slower than it was in August,


493
0:26:14,4 --> 0:26:16,194
and August was slower than it was in July.


494
0:26:16,194 --> 0:26:18,11
We're heading in the wrong direction.


495
0:26:18,11 --> 0:26:22,359
23 million Americans are struggling for work today.


496
0:26:22,359 --> 0:26:26,184
15% of Americans are living in poverty today.


497
0:26:26,184 --> 0:26:29,53
This is not what a real recovery looks like.


498
0:26:29,53 --> 0:26:31,973
We need real reforms for a real recovery,


499
0:26:31,973 --> 0:26:34,658
and that's exactly what Mitt Romney and I are proposing.


500
0:26:34,658 --> 0:26:36,281
It's 5-Point plan.


501
0:26:36,281 --> 0:26:39,498
Get America energy-independent in North America by the end of the decade.


502
0:26:39,498 --> 0:26:43,609
Help people who are hurting get the skills they need to get the jobs they want.


503
0:26:43,609 --> 0:26:46,51
Get this deficit and debt under control to prevent a debt crisis.


504
0:26:46,51 --> 0:26:49,566
Make trade work for America so we can make more things in America


505
0:26:49,566 --> 0:26:52,548
and sell them overseas and champion small businesses.


506
0:26:52,548 --> 0:26:55,596
Don't raise taxes on small businesses, because they're our job creators.


507
0:26:55,596 --> 0:26:59,303
He talks about Detroit. Mitt Romney's a car guy.


508
0:26:59,303 --> 0:27:3,353
They keep misquoting him, but let me tell you about the Mitt Romney I know.


509
0:27:3,353 --> 0:27:5,651
This is a guy who


510
0:27:5,651 --> 0:27:9,226
— I was talking to a family in Northborough, Massachusetts the other day,


511
0:27:9,226 --> 0:27:11,695
Cheryl and Mark Nixon (sp).


512
0:27:11,695 --> 0:27:14,942
Their kids were hit in a car crash, 4 of them


513
0:27:14,942 --> 0:27:17,382
— 2 of them, Rob (sp) and Reid (sp), were paralyzed.


514
0:27:17,382 --> 0:27:19,536
The Romneys didn't know them. They went to the same church.


515
0:27:19,536 --> 0:27:20,636
They never met before.


516
0:27:20,636 --> 0:27:23,14
Mitt asked if he could come over on Christmas.


517
0:27:23,14 --> 0:27:27,395
He brought his boys, his wife and gifts.


518
0:27:27,395 --> 0:27:30,631
Later on he said, I know you're struggling, Mark (sp).


519
0:27:30,631 --> 0:27:32,716
Don't worry about their college; I'll pay for it.


520
0:27:32,716 --> 0:27:34,277
When Mark (sp) told me this story


521
0:27:34,277 --> 0:27:36,347
— because you know what, Mitt Romney doesn't tell these stories.


522
0:27:36,347 --> 0:27:37,554
The Nixons told this story.


523
0:27:37,554 --> 0:27:41,721
When he told me this story, he said it wasn't the help — the cash help;


524
0:27:41,721 --> 0:27:44,509
it's that he gave his time, and he has consistently.


525
0:27:44,509 --> 0:27:48,121
This is a man who gave 30% of his income to charity,


526
0:27:48,121 --> 0:27:49,667
more than the 2 of us combined.


527
0:27:49,667 --> 0:27:51,459
Mitt Romney's a good man.


528
0:27:51,459 --> 0:27:55,24
He cares about 100% of Americans in this country.


529
0:27:55,24 --> 0:27:56,786
And with respect to that quote,


530
0:27:56,786 --> 0:27:59,311
I think the vice president very well knows


531
0:27:59,311 --> 0:28:5,786
that sometimes the words don't come out of your mouth the right way. (Laughter.)


532
0:28:5,786 --> 0:28:7,471
[Biden] But I always say what I mean.


533
0:28:7,471 --> 0:28:9,281
[Raddatz] You —


534
0:28:9,281 --> 0:28:10,258
[Biden] And so does Romney.


535
0:28:10,258 --> 0:28:11,589
[Ryan] We want everybody to succeed.


536
0:28:11,589 --> 0:28:14,751
We want to get people out of poverty, in the middle class,


537
0:28:14,751 --> 0:28:15,866
on to lives of self-sufficiency.


538
0:28:15,866 --> 0:28:18,54
We believe in opportunity and upward mobility.


539
0:28:18,54 --> 0:28:20,62
That's what we're going to push for in a Romney administration.


540
0:28:20,62 --> 0:28:21,285
[Raddatz] Vice President?


541
0:28:21,285 --> 0:28:21,816
[Biden] Look —


542
0:28:21,816 --> 0:28:23,271
[Raddatz] I have a feeling you have a few things to say here. (Laughter.)


543
0:28:23,271 --> 0:28:26,72
[Biden] (Chuckles.) The idea, if you heard that


544
0:28:26,72 --> 0:28:31,555
— that little soliloquy on 47%, and you think he just made a mistake,


545
0:28:31,555 --> 0:28:36,29
then I think you're — I — I — I — I — I got a bridge to sell you.


546
0:28:36,29 --> 0:28:42,637
Look, I don't doubt his personal generosity, and I understand what it's like.


547
0:28:42,637 --> 0:28:45,768
When I was a little younger than the congressman,


548
0:28:45,768 --> 0:28:51,685
my wife was in an accident, killed my daughter and my wife,


549
0:28:51,685 --> 0:28:53,154
and my 2 sons survived.


550
0:28:53,154 --> 0:28:57,284
I have sat in the homes of many people who've gone through what I get through


551
0:28:57,284 --> 0:28:59,307
because the one thing you can give people solace


552
0:28:59,307 --> 0:29:4,276
is to know they know you've been through it, that they can make it.


553
0:29:4,276 --> 0:29:8,663
So I don't doubt his personal commitment to individuals.


554
0:29:8,663 --> 0:29:13,485
But you know what? I know he had no commitment to the automobile industry.


555
0:29:13,485 --> 0:29:18,13
He just let — he said, let it go bankrupt, period, let it drop out.


556
0:29:18,13 --> 0:29:20,414
All this talk — we saved a million jobs.


557
0:29:20,414 --> 0:29:23,49
200 thousand people are working today.


558
0:29:23,49 --> 0:29:26,996
And I have never met 2 guys who are more down on America across the board.


559
0:29:26,996 --> 0:29:28,696
We're told everything is going bad.


560
0:29:28,696 --> 0:29:32,842
We have 5.2 million new jobs, private sector jobs.


561
0:29:32,842 --> 0:29:36,305
We need more, but 5.2 million — if they'd get out of the way,


562
0:29:36,305 --> 0:29:40,27
if they get out of the way and let us pass the tax cut for the middle class,


563
0:29:40,27 --> 0:29:41,204
make it permanent,


564
0:29:41,204 --> 0:29:44,65
if they get out of the way and pass the — pass the jobs bill,


565
0:29:44,65 --> 0:29:46,452
if they get out of the way and let us allow 14 million people


566
0:29:46,452 --> 0:29:50,619
who are struggling to stay in their homes because their mortgages are upside-down,


567
0:29:50,619 --> 0:29:53,972
but they never missed a mortgage payment — just get out of the way.


568
0:29:53,972 --> 0:29:56,899
Stop talking about how you care about people.


569
0:29:56,899 --> 0:29:59,747
Show me something. Show me a policy.


570
0:29:59,747 --> 0:30:3,107
Show me a policy where you take responsibility.


571
0:30:3,107 --> 0:30:5,993
And by the way, they talk about this Great Recession


572
0:30:5,993 --> 0:30:9,58
as if it fell out of the sky, like, oh my goodness, where did it come from?


573
0:30:9,58 --> 0:30:14,11
It came from this man voting to put 2 wars in a credit card,


574
0:30:14,11 --> 0:30:17,945
to at the same time put a prescription drug benefit on the credit card,


575
0:30:17,945 --> 0:30:21,179
a trillion- dollar tax cut for a — very wealthy.


576
0:30:21,179 --> 0:30:24,689
I was there. I voted against him. I said, no, we can't afford that.


577
0:30:24,689 --> 0:30:30,52
And now all of a sudden these guys are so seized with a concern about the debt


578
0:30:30,52 --> 0:30:31,297
that they created —


579
0:30:31,297 --> 0:30:33,874
[Raddatz] Congressman Ryan.


580
0:30:33,874 --> 0:30:38,478
[Ryan] Let's not forget that they came in with one-party control.


581
0:30:38,478 --> 0:30:40,995
When Barack Obama was elected, his party controlled everything.


582
0:30:40,995 --> 0:30:43,128
They had the ability to do everything of their choosing,


583
0:30:43,128 --> 0:30:45,736
and look at where we are right now.


584
0:30:45,736 --> 0:30:50,597
They passed a stimulus, the idea that we could borrow $831 billion,


585
0:30:50,597 --> 0:30:52,251
spend it on all these special interest groups


586
0:30:52,251 --> 0:30:53,967
and that it would work out just fine,


587
0:30:53,967 --> 0:30:56,338
that unemployment would never get to 8%.


588
0:30:56,338 --> 0:30:58,208
It went up above 8% for 43 months.


589
0:30:58,208 --> 0:31:0,677
They said that right now, if we just pass this stimulus,


590
0:31:0,677 --> 0:31:4,144
the economy would grow at 4%. It's growing at 1.3 (%).


591
0:31:4,144 --> 0:31:6,328
[Raddatz]: When could you get it below 6%?


592
0:31:6,328 --> 0:31:9,484
[Ryan] That's what our entire premise of our pro-growth plan


593
0:31:9,484 --> 0:31:11,92
for a stronger middle class is all about:


594
0:31:11,92 --> 0:31:13,161
getting the economy growing at 4%,


595
0:31:13,161 --> 0:31:15,765
creating 12 million jobs over the next 4 years.


596
0:31:15,765 --> 0:31:18,176
Look at just the $90 billion in stimulus,


597
0:31:18,176 --> 0:31:20,675
and — and the vice president was in charge of overseeing this,


598
0:31:20,675 --> 0:31:25,987
$90 billion in green pork to campaign contributors and special interest groups.


599
0:31:25,987 --> 0:31:30,781
There are just at the Department of Energy over 100 criminal investigations


600
0:31:30,781 --> 0:31:32,81
that have been launched into just how —


601
0:31:32,81 --> 0:31:32,581
[Biden] Martha —


602
0:31:32,581 --> 0:31:33,81
[Ryan] — stimulus — (inaudible) — are being spent —


603
0:31:33,81 --> 0:31:33,812
[Raddatz] Go ahead.


604
0:31:33,812 --> 0:31:34,481
Go ahead, Vice —


605
0:31:34,481 --> 0:31:37,274
[Biden] Martha, look. His colleague runs an investigative committee —


606
0:31:37,274 --> 0:31:38,205
[Ryan] Crony capitalism — (inaudible).


607
0:31:38,205 --> 0:31:39,764
[Biden] — spent months and months and months going into this —


608
0:31:39,764 --> 0:31:42,79
[Ryan] This is the — this is the inspector general.


609
0:31:42,79 --> 0:31:43,272
[Biden] — months and months.


610
0:31:43,272 --> 0:31:47,802
They found no evidence of cronyism. And I love my friend here.


611
0:31:47,802 --> 0:31:50,82
I — I'm not allowed to show letters, but go on our website:


612
0:31:50,82 --> 0:31:53,584
He sent me 2 letters saying, by the way,


613
0:31:53,584 --> 0:31:59,134
can you send me some stimulus money for companies here in the state of Wisconsin?


614
0:31:59,134 --> 0:32:1,619
We sent millions of dollars. You know why he said he needed —


615
0:32:1,619 --> 0:32:3,73
[Raddatz] You did ask for stimulus money, correct?


616
0:32:3,73 --> 0:32:3,988
[Biden] Sure he did. By the way — (inaudible) —


617
0:32:3,988 --> 0:32:8,28
[Ryan] On 2 occasions, we — we — we advocated for constituents who were applying for grants.


618
0:32:8,28 --> 0:32:9,205
[Biden] (Chuckles.)


619
0:32:9,205 --> 0:32:11,389
[Ryan] That's what we do. We do that for all constituents who are — (inaudible) — for grants.


620
0:32:11,389 --> 0:32:12,628
[Biden] I love that. I love that.


621
0:32:12,628 --> 0:32:16,189
This is such a bad program, and he writes me a letter saying


622
0:32:16,189 --> 0:32:17,951
— writes the Department of Energy a letter saying,


623
0:32:17,951 --> 0:32:21,891
the reason we need this stimulus — it will create growth and jobs.


624
0:32:21,891 --> 0:32:23,883
He — his words.


625
0:32:23,883 --> 0:32:27,762
And now he's sitting here looking at me — and by the way, that program


626
0:32:27,762 --> 0:32:32,185
— again, investigated — what the Congress said was, it was a model:


627
0:32:32,185 --> 0:32:37,161
less than 4/10 of 1% waste or fraud in the program.


628
0:32:37,161 --> 0:32:41,45
And all this talk about cronyism — they investigated and investigated;


629
0:32:41,45 --> 0:32:43,39
did not find one single piece of evidence.


630
0:32:43,39 --> 0:32:46,533
I wish he would just tell — be a little more candid.


631
0:32:46,533 --> 0:32:53,574
[Ryan] Was it a good idea to spend taxpayer dollars on electric cars in Finland or on windmills in China?


632
0:32:53,574 --> 0:32:54,412
[Biden] Look —


633
0:32:54,412 --> 0:32:57,324
[Ryan] Was it a good idea to borrow all this money from countries like China —


634
0:32:57,324 --> 0:32:58,224
[Biden] (Chuckles.)


635
0:32:58,224 --> 0:33:0,164
[Ryan] — and spend it on all these various different interest groups?


636
0:33:0,164 --> 0:33:2,209
[Biden] Let me tell you it was a good idea. It was a good idea


637
0:33:2,209 --> 0:33:5,52
— Moody's and others said that this was exactly what we needed


638
0:33:5,52 --> 0:33:7,174
that stopped us from going off the cliff.


639
0:33:7,174 --> 0:33:9,604
It set the conditions to be able to grow again.


640
0:33:9,604 --> 0:33:13,764
We have — in fact, 4% of those green jobs didn't go under


641
0:33:13,764 --> 0:33:15,65
— or went — went — went under — didn't work.


642
0:33:15,65 --> 0:33:18,3
It's a better batting average than investment bankers have.


643
0:33:18,3 --> 0:33:20,429
They have about a 40% — (inaudible) — loss.


644
0:33:20,429 --> 0:33:22,207
[Ryan] Where are the 5 million green jobs that were being promised —


645
0:33:22,207 --> 0:33:25,281
[Raddatz] I want to move on here to Medicare and entitlements.


646
0:33:25,281 --> 0:33:28,627
I think we've gone over this quite enough. And both —


647
0:33:28,627 --> 0:33:30,573
[Biden] And by the way, any letter you send me I'll entertain.


648
0:33:30,573 --> 0:33:33,725
[Ryan] I appreciate that, Joe. (Laughter.)


649
0:33:33,725 --> 0:33:35,747
[Raddatz] Let's talk about Medicare and entitlements.


650
0:33:35,747 --> 0:33:38,564
Both Medicare and Social Security are going broke


651
0:33:38,564 --> 0:33:41,398
and taking a larger share of the budget in the process.


652
0:33:41,398 --> 0:33:44,677
Will benefits for Americans under these programs


653
0:33:44,677 --> 0:33:49,124
have to change for the programs to survive, Mr. Ryan?


654
0:33:49,124 --> 0:33:51,145
[Ryan] Absolutely. Medicare and Social Security are going bankrupt.


655
0:33:51,145 --> 0:33:52,629
These are indisputable facts.


656
0:33:52,629 --> 0:33:57,295
Look, when I look at these programs, we've all had tragedies in our lives.


657
0:33:57,295 --> 0:34:0,814
I think about what they've done for my own family.


658
0:34:0,814 --> 0:34:4,519
My mom and I had my grandmother move in with us who was facing Alzheimer's.


659
0:34:4,519 --> 0:34:7,343
Medicare was there for her, just like it's there for my mom right now


660
0:34:7,343 --> 0:34:8,55
who's a Florida senior.


661
0:34:8,55 --> 0:34:12,39
After my dad died, my mom and I got Social Security survivors benefits.


662
0:34:12,39 --> 0:34:13,505
Helped me pay for college.


663
0:34:13,505 --> 0:34:15,645
It helped her go back to college in her 50s,


664
0:34:15,645 --> 0:34:19,465
where she started a small business because of the new skills she got.


665
0:34:19,465 --> 0:34:22,433
She paid all of her taxes on the promise


666
0:34:22,433 --> 0:34:24,823
that these programs would be there for her.


667
0:34:24,823 --> 0:34:26,261
We will honor this promise.


668
0:34:26,261 --> 0:34:29,11
And the best way to do it is reform it for my generation.


669
0:34:29,11 --> 0:34:34,129
You see, if you reform these programs for my generation, people 54 and below,


670
0:34:34,129 --> 0:34:37,56
you can guarantee they don't change for people in or near retirement,


671
0:34:37,56 --> 0:34:40,174
which is precisely what Mitt Romney and I are proposing.


672
0:34:40,174 --> 0:34:42,338
Look at what — look what "Obamacare" does.


673
0:34:42,338 --> 0:34:48,311
"Obamacare" takes $716 billion from Medicare to spend on "Obamacare."


674
0:34:48,311 --> 0:34:52,49
Even their own chief actuary at Medicare backs this up.


675
0:34:52,49 --> 0:34:54,83
He says you can't spend the same dollar twice.


676
0:34:54,83 --> 0:34:58,115
You can't claim that this money goes to Medicare and "Obamacare."


677
0:34:58,115 --> 0:35:0,92
And then they put this new "Obamacare" board


678
0:35:0,92 --> 0:35:2,913
in charge of cutting Medicare each and every year


679
0:35:2,913 --> 0:35:6,273
in ways that will lead to denied care for current seniors.


680
0:35:6,273 --> 0:35:8,142
This board, by the way, it's 15 people.


681
0:35:8,142 --> 0:35:10,34
The president's supposed to appoint them next year.


682
0:35:10,34 --> 0:35:13,99
And not one of them even has to have medical training.


683
0:35:13,99 --> 0:35:15,807
And Social Security, if we don't shore up Social Security,


684
0:35:15,807 --> 0:35:19,89
when we run out of the IOUs, when the program goes bankrupt,


685
0:35:19,89 --> 0:35:23,25
a 25% across-the-board benefit cut kicks in on current seniors


686
0:35:23,25 --> 0:35:24,565
in the middle of their retirement.


687
0:35:24,565 --> 0:35:26,557
We're going to stop that from happening.


688
0:35:26,557 --> 0:35:29,849
They haven't put a credible solution on the table.


689
0:35:29,849 --> 0:35:32,141
He'll tell you about vouchers.


690
0:35:32,141 --> 0:35:34,966
He'll say all these things to try and scare people.


691
0:35:34,966 --> 0:35:36,558
Here's what we're saying:


692
0:35:36,558 --> 0:35:39,853
Give younger people, when they become Medicare-eligible,


693
0:35:39,853 --> 0:35:43,356
guaranteed coverage options that you can't be denied,


694
0:35:43,356 --> 0:35:45,87
including traditional Medicare.


695
0:35:45,87 --> 0:35:47,874
