like they're — they're proposing —


1174
0:54:4,618 --> 0:54:6,686
[Biden] They're going to increase it $2 billion — $2 trillion.


1175
0:54:6,686 --> 0:54:8,46
[Ryan] That's not accurate. We're talking about preventing —


1176
0:54:8,46 --> 0:54:11,46
[Raddatz] More than that. No — so no massive defense increase?


1177
0:54:11,46 --> 0:54:11,823
[Ryan] No, we're saying is, don't —


1178
0:54:11,823 --> 0:54:12,646
OK, you want to get into defense now?


1179
0:54:12,646 --> 0:54:14,187
[Raddatz] Let — yes, I do. I do —


1180
0:54:14,187 --> 0:54:15,149
[Ryan] All right. So —


1181
0:54:15,149 --> 0:54:15,741
[Raddatz] — because that's another math question.


1182
0:54:15,741 --> 0:54:16,241
[Ryan] Right. OK.


1183
0:54:16,241 --> 0:54:17,28
[Raddatz] How do you do that?


1184
0:54:17,28 --> 0:54:21,614
[Ryan] So they proposed a $478 (sic) billion cut to defense


1185
0:54:21,614 --> 0:54:22,39
to begin with.


1186
0:54:22,39 --> 0:54:25,759
Now we have another $500 billion cut to defense


1187
0:54:25,759 --> 0:54:27,505
that's lurking on the horizon.


1188
0:54:27,505 --> 0:54:31,383
They insisted upon that cut being involved in the debt negotiations —


1189
0:54:31,383 --> 0:54:32,13
[Raddatz] Let —


1190
0:54:32,13 --> 0:54:33,137
[Ryan] — and now we have a $1 trillion cut —


1191
0:54:33,137 --> 0:54:35,95
[Raddatz] Let's put the automatic defense cuts aside. OK?


1192
0:54:35,95 --> 0:54:35,872
[Ryan] Right. OK.


1193
0:54:35,872 --> 0:54:37,526
[Raddatz] Let's put those aside. No one wants that.


1194
0:54:37,526 --> 0:54:38,41
[Biden] I'd like to go back to that.


1195
0:54:38,41 --> 0:54:38,541
[Ryan] OK.


1196
0:54:38,541 --> 0:54:39,841
[Raddatz] But I want to know how you do the math


1197
0:54:39,841 --> 0:54:41,896
and have this increase in defense spending?


1198
0:54:41,896 --> 0:54:43,18
[Biden] 2 trillion dollars.


1199
0:54:43,18 --> 0:54:45,156
[Ryan] You don't cut defense by a trillion dollars.


1200
0:54:45,156 --> 0:54:46,471
That's what we're talking about. The additional trillion —


1201
0:54:46,471 --> 0:54:49,722
[Raddatz] And what national security issues justify an increase?


1202
0:54:49,722 --> 0:54:50,729
[Biden] Who's cutting it by a trillion?


1203
0:54:50,729 --> 0:54:54,896
[Ryan] We're going to cut 80,000 soldiers, 20,000 Marines,


1204
0:54:54,896 --> 0:54:58,263
120 cargo planes.


1205
0:54:58,263 --> 0:54:59,348
We're going to push the Joint Strike Fighter out.


1206
0:54:59,348 --> 0:55:0,694
[Raddatz] Drawing down in one war —


1207
0:55:0,694 --> 0:55:1,886
[Ryan] We're cutting missile defense.


1208
0:55:1,886 --> 0:55:2,478
[Raddatz] — and one war — (inaudible ) —


1209
0:55:2,478 --> 0:55:5,562
[Ryan] If these cuts go through, our Navy will be the small it is


1210
0:55:5,562 --> 0:55:8,876
— it — the smallest it has been since before World War I.


1211
0:55:8,876 --> 0:55:11,502
This invites weakness.


1212
0:55:11,502 --> 0:55:12,51
Look, do we believe in peace through strength?


1213
0:55:12,51 --> 0:55:13,164
You bet we do.


1214
0:55:13,164 --> 0:55:17,701
And that means you don't impose these devastating cuts on our military.


1215
0:55:17,701 --> 0:55:21,412
So we're saying don't cut the military by a trillion dollars,


1216
0:55:21,412 --> 0:55:24,521
not increase it by a trillion, don't cut it by a trillion dollars.


1217
0:55:24,521 --> 0:55:26,74
[Raddatz] Quickly, Vice President Biden, on this, and I want to move on.


1218
0:55:26,74 --> 0:55:28,24
[Biden] Look, we don't cut it.


1219
0:55:28,24 --> 0:55:29,227
And I might add this so-called


1220
0:55:29,227 --> 0:55:33,179
— I know we don't want to use the fancy word "sequester," this automatic cut —


1221
0:55:33,179 --> 0:55:35,875
that was part of a debt deal that they asked for.


1222
0:55:35,875 --> 0:55:38,705
And let me tell you what my friend said at a press conference


1223
0:55:38,705 --> 0:55:40,574
announcing his support of the deal.


1224
0:55:40,574 --> 0:55:45,115
He said — and I'm — we've been looking for this moment for a long time. (Inaudible) —


1225
0:55:45,115 --> 0:55:47,92
[Ryan] Can I tell you what that meant?


1226
0:55:47,92 --> 0:55:47,592
[Biden] Why —


1227
0:55:47,592 --> 0:55:49,107
[Ryan] We've been looking for bipartisanship for a long time.


1228
0:55:49,107 --> 0:55:51,587
[Biden] And so the bipartisanship is what he voted for:


1229
0:55:51,587 --> 0:55:54,225
the automatic cuts in defense if they didn't act.


1230
0:55:54,225 --> 0:55:56,306
And beyond that, they asked for another —


1231
0:55:56,306 --> 0:56:1,104
look, the military says, we need a smaller, leaner Army.


1232
0:56:1,104 --> 0:56:2,697
We need more special forces.


1233
0:56:2,697 --> 0:56:6,833
We need — we don't need more M1 tanks. What we need is more UAVs.


1234
0:56:6,833 --> 0:56:7,764
[Raddatz] Some of the military — I know that's — (inaudible) —


1235
0:56:7,764 --> 0:56:9,2
[Biden] Not some of the military;


1236
0:56:9,2 --> 0:56:13,281
that was the decision of the Joint Chiefs of Staff,


1237
0:56:13,281 --> 0:56:16,688
recommended to us and agreed to by the president.


1238
0:56:16,688 --> 0:56:17,588
That's a fact.


1239
0:56:17,588 --> 0:56:18,98
[Raddatz] Who answers to the civilian leaders.


1240
0:56:18,98 --> 0:56:20,747
[Biden] They made the recommendation first.


1241
0:56:20,747 --> 0:56:22,741
[Raddatz] OK. Let's move on to Afghanistan.


1242
0:56:22,741 --> 0:56:23,98
[Ryan] Can I get into that for a second?


1243
0:56:23,98 --> 0:56:25,572
[Raddatz] I'd like to move on to Afghanistan, please.


1244
0:56:25,572 --> 0:56:26,72
[Ryan] OK.


1245
0:56:26,72 --> 0:56:29,139
[Raddatz] And that's one of the biggest expenditures this country has made,


1246
0:56:29,139 --> 0:56:32,122
in dollars and, more importantly, in lives.


1247
0:56:32,122 --> 0:56:37,755
We just passed the sad milestone of losing 2,000 U.S. troops there in this war.


1248
0:56:37,755 --> 0:56:40,569
More than 50 of them were killed this year


1249
0:56:40,569 --> 0:56:43,817
by the very Afghan forces we are trying to help.


1250
0:56:43,817 --> 0:56:47,73
Now, we've reached the recruiting goal for Afghan forces.


1251
0:56:47,73 --> 0:56:49,707
We've degraded al-Qaida.


1252
0:56:49,707 --> 0:56:52,235
So tell me, why not leave now?


1253
0:56:52,235 --> 0:56:54,649
What more can we really accomplish?


1254
0:56:54,649 --> 0:56:57,442
Is it worth more American lives?


1255
0:56:57,442 --> 0:56:59,627
[Ryan] We don't want to lose the gains we've gotten.


1256
0:56:59,627 --> 0:57:3,752
We want to make sure that the Taliban does not come back in


1257
0:57:3,752 --> 0:57:5,76
and give al- Qaida a safe haven.


1258
0:57:5,76 --> 0:57:9,137
We agree with the administration on their 2014 transition.


1259
0:57:9,137 --> 0:57:11,413
Look, when I think about Afghanistan,


1260
0:57:11,413 --> 0:57:15,11
I think about the incredible job that our troops have done.


1261
0:57:15,11 --> 0:57:17,295
You've been there more than the 2 of us combined.


1262
0:57:17,295 --> 0:57:19,473
First time I was there in 2002,


1263
0:57:19,473 --> 0:57:21,729
it was amazing to me what they were facing.


1264
0:57:21,729 --> 0:57:26,14
When I went to the Arghandab Valley in Kandahar before the surge,


1265
0:57:26,14 --> 0:57:28,32
I sat down with a young private in the 82nd


1266
0:57:28,32 --> 0:57:29,939
from the Menominee Indian Reservation


1267
0:57:29,939 --> 0:57:33,133
who would tell me what he did every day, and I was in awe.


1268
0:57:33,133 --> 0:57:35,33
And to see what they had in front of them


1269
0:57:35,33 --> 0:57:36,641
— and then to go back there in December,


1270
0:57:36,641 --> 0:57:38,195
to go throughout Helmand with the Marines


1271
0:57:38,195 --> 0:57:39,556
to see what they had accomplished


1272
0:57:39,556 --> 0:57:41,811
— it's nothing short of amazing.


1273
0:57:41,811 --> 0:57:45,867
What we don't want to do is lose the gains we've gotten.


1274
0:57:45,867 --> 0:57:49,123
Now, we've disagreed from time to time on a few issues.


1275
0:57:49,123 --> 0:57:51,437
We would have more likely taken into account


1276
0:57:51,437 --> 0:57:55,765
the recommendations from our commanders, General Petraeus, Admiral Mullen,


1277
0:57:55,765 --> 0:57:59,156
on troop levels throughout this year's fighting season.


1278
0:57:59,156 --> 0:58:1,721
We've been skeptical about negotiations with the Taliban,


1279
0:58:1,721 --> 0:58:3,667
especially while they're shooting at us.


1280
0:58:3,667 --> 0:58:7,928
But we want to see the 2014 transition be successful.


1281
0:58:7,928 --> 0:58:12,399
And that means we want to make sure our commanders have what they need


1282
0:58:12,399 --> 0:58:14,191
to make sure that it is successful


1283
0:58:14,191 --> 0:58:18,14
so that this does not once again become a launching pad for terrorists.


1284
0:58:18,14 --> 0:58:19,508
[Raddatz] Vice President Biden.


1285
0:58:19,508 --> 0:58:21,208
[Biden] Martha, let's keep our eye on the ball.


1286
0:58:21,208 --> 0:58:25,297
The reason I've been in and out of Afghanistan and Iraq 20 times


1287
0:58:25,297 --> 0:58:27,266
— I've been up in the Kunar valley —


1288
0:58:27,266 --> 0:58:30,752
I've been throughout that whole country, mostly in a helicopter


1289
0:58:30,752 --> 0:58:33,698
and sometimes in a vehicle.


1290
0:58:33,698 --> 0:58:36,13
The fact is we went there for one reason:


1291
0:58:36,13 --> 0:58:40,402
to get those people who killed Americans, al-Qaida.


1292
0:58:40,402 --> 0:58:42,718
We've decimated al-Qaida central.


1293
0:58:42,718 --> 0:58:47,663
We have eliminated Osama bin Laden. That was our purpose.


1294
0:58:47,663 --> 0:58:50,642
And in fact, in the meantime, what we said we would do,


1295
0:58:50,642 --> 0:58:54,652
we would help train the Afghan military.


1296
0:58:54,652 --> 0:58:59,83
It's their responsibility to take over their own security.


1297
0:58:59,83 --> 0:59:4,356
That's why, with 49 of our allies in Afghanistan,


1298
0:59:4,356 --> 0:59:10,255
we've agreed on a gradual drawdown so we're out of there by the year twenty -


1299
0:59:10,255 --> 0:59:12,34
— in the year 2014.


1300
0:59:12,34 --> 0:59:15,903
My friend and the governor say it's based on conditions,


1301
0:59:15,903 --> 0:59:17,541
which means it depends.


1302
0:59:17,541 --> 0:59:20,67
It does not depend for us.


1303
0:59:20,67 --> 0:59:25,817
It is the responsibility of the Afghans to take care of their own security.


1304
0:59:25,817 --> 0:59:30,9
We have trained over 315,000, mostly without incident.


1305
0:59:30,9 --> 0:59:34,132
There have been more than 2 dozen cases of green on blue


1306
0:59:34,132 --> 0:59:35,985
where Americans have been killed.


1307
0:59:35,985 --> 0:59:40,892
If we do — if the — if the measures the military has taken do not take hold,


1308
0:59:40,892 --> 0:59:44,359
we will not go on joint patrols, we will not train in the field.


1309
0:59:44,359 --> 0:59:50,765
We'll only train in the — in the Army bases that exist there.


1310
0:59:50,765 --> 0:59:52,388
But we are leaving.


1311
0:59:52,388 --> 0:59:56,886
We are leaving in 2014, period.


1312
0:59:56,886 --> 1:0:0,345
And in the process, we're going to be saving over the next 10 years


1313
1:0:0,345 --> 1:0:2,957
another $800 billion.


1314
1:0:2,957 --> 1:0:5,568
We've been in this war for over a decade.


1315
1:0:5,568 --> 1:0:9,278
The primary objective is almost completed.


1316
1:0:9,278 --> 1:0:13,968
Now all we're doing is putting the Kabul government in a position


1317
1:0:13,968 --> 1:0:16,815
to be able to maintain their own security.


1318
1:0:16,815 --> 1:0:20,52
It's their responsibility, not America's.


1319
1:0:20,52 --> 1:0:24,737
[Raddatz] What conditions could justify staying, Congressman Ryan?


1320
1:0:24,737 --> 1:0:25,73
[Ryan] We don't want to stay.


1321
1:0:25,73 --> 1:0:30,19
We want — look, one of my best friends in Janesville, a reservist,


1322
1:0:30,19 --> 1:0:33,577
is at a forward operating base in Eastern Afghanistan right now.


1323
1:0:33,577 --> 1:0:36,47
Our wives are best friends, our daughters are best friends.


1324
1:0:36,47 --> 1:0:40,359
I want — I want him and all of our troops to come home


1325
1:0:40,359 --> 1:0:42,676
as soon and safely as possible.


1326
1:0:42,676 --> 1:0:45,263
We want to make sure that 2014 is successful.


1327
1:0:45,263 --> 1:0:48,244
That's why we want to make sure that we give our commanders


1328
1:0:48,244 --> 1:0:50,648
what they say they need to make it successful.


1329
1:0:50,648 --> 1:0:53,946
We don't want to extend beyond 2014. That's the point we're making.


1330
1:0:53,946 --> 1:0:58,38
You know, if it was just this, I feel like we would


1331
1:0:58,38 --> 1:1:2,345
— we would be able to call this a success, but it's not.


1332
1:1:2,345 --> 1:1:6,601
What we are witnessing as we turn on our television screens these days,


1333
1:1:6,601 --> 1:1:10,217
is the absolute unraveling of the Obama foreign policy.


1334
1:1:10,217 --> 1:1:13,488
Problems are growing at home, but jobs


1335
1:1:13,488 --> 1:1:14,634
— problems are growing abroad –


1336
1:1:14,634 --> 1:1:17,22
but jobs aren't growing here at home.


1337
1:1:17,22 --> 1:1:17,968
[Raddatz] Let me go back to this.


1338
1:1:17,968 --> 1:1:22,824
He says we're absolutely leaving in 2014.


1339
1:1:22,824 --> 1:1:25,448
You're saying that's not an absolute,


1340
1:1:25,448 --> 1:1:26,71
but you won't talk about what conditions would justify —


1341
1:1:26,71 --> 1:1:27,355
[Ryan] Do you know why we say that?


1342
1:1:27,355 --> 1:1:28,671
Do you know why we say that?


1343
1:1:28,671 --> 1:1:29,709
[Biden] I'd like to know why.


1344
1:1:29,709 --> 1:1:31,532
[Ryan] Because we don't want to broadcast to our enemies,


1345
1:1:31,532 --> 1:1:33,632
put a date on your calendar,


1346
1:1:33,632 --> 1:1:35,532
wait us out and then come back.


1347
1:1:35,532 --> 1:1:36,94
We want to make sure —


1348
1:1:36,94 --> 1:1:37,86
[Raddatz] But you agree with the timeline?


1349
1:1:37,86 --> 1:1:40,801
[Ryan] We do — we do agree with the timeline in the transition,


1350
1:1:40,801 --> 1:1:44,488
but what we — what any administration will do in 2013


1351
1:1:44,488 --> 1:1:49,57
is assess the situation to see how best to complete this timeline.


1352
1:1:49,57 --> 1:1:49,68
What we do not want to do —


1353
1:1:49,68 --> 1:1:51,831
[Biden] We will leave in 2014.


1354
1:1:51,831 --> 1:1:55,483
[Ryan] What we do not want to do is give our allies reason


1355
1:1:55,483 --> 1:1:59,549
to trust us less and our enemies more —


1356
1:1:59,549 --> 1:2:1,295
we don't want to embolden our enemies


1357
1:2:1,295 --> 1:2:3,887
to hold and wait out for us and then take over the —


1358
1:2:3,887 --> 1:2:5,316
[Biden] Martha, that's a bizarre statement.


1359
1:2:5,316 --> 1:2:6,37
[Ryan] That's why we want to make sure


1360
1:2:6,37 --> 1:2:7,332
— no, that's why we want to make sure that this — that —


1361
1:2:7,332 --> 1:2:9,713
[Biden] That's a bizarre statement, since 49 of our allies — hear me,


1362
1:2:9,713 --> 1:2:15,2
49 of our allies signed onto this position, 49.


1363
1:2:15,2 --> 1:2:17,58
[Ryan] And we're reading that they want to pull out early.


1364
1:2:17,58 --> 1:2:21,781
[Biden] 49. 49 of our allies said out in 2014.


1365
1:2:21,781 --> 1:2:24,78
It's the responsibility of the Afghans.


1366
1:2:24,78 --> 1:2:25,147
We have other responsibilities —


1367
1:2:25,147 --> 1:2:25,662
[Ryan] Which is — which is — which is what we agree with.


1368
1:2:25,662 --> 1:2:29,308
[Raddatz] Do you — do you think that this timeline — but we have — we have soldiers and Marines —


1369
1:2:29,308 --> 1:2:30,469
[Biden] (Theirs are sufficient. ?)


1370
1:2:30,469 --> 1:2:34,695
[Raddatz] We have Afghan forces murdering our forces over there.


1371
1:2:34,695 --> 1:2:38,967
The Taliban is, do you think, taking advantage of this timeline?


1372
1:2:38,967 --> 1:2:43,169
[Biden] Well, look, the Taliban — what we've found out —


1373
1:2:43,169 --> 1:2:45,85
and we — you — you saw it in Iraq, Martha.


1374
1:2:45,85 --> 1:2:47,293
Unless you set a timeline,


1375
1:2:47,293 --> 1:2:54,175
Baghdad in the case of Iraq and — and Kabul in the case of Afghanistan


1376
1:2:54,175 --> 1:2:55,429
will not step up.


1377
1:2:55,429 --> 1:2:57,998
They're happy to let us continue to do the job —


1378
1:2:57,998 --> 1:3:0,373
international security forces to do the job.


1379
1:3:0,373 --> 1:3:4,588
The only way they step up is say, fellas, we're leaving;


1380
1:3:4,588 --> 1:3:8,404
we've trained you; step up. Step up.


1381
1:3:8,404 --> 1:3:9,366
[Raddatz] But let me — let me go back —


1382
1:3:9,366 --> 1:3:10,943
[Biden] That's the only way it works.


1383
1:3:10,943 --> 1:3:14,142
[Raddatz] Let me go back to the surge troops that we put in there.


1384
1:3:14,142 --> 1:3:16,973
And you brought this up, Congressman Ryan.


1385
1:3:16,973 --> 1:3:18,704
I have talked to a lot of troops.


1386
1:3:18,704 --> 1:3:21,814
I've talked to senior officers who were concerned


1387
1:3:21,814 --> 1:3:26,188
that the surge troops were pulled out during the fighting season,


1388
1:3:26,188 --> 1:3:30,303
and some of them saw that as a political — as a political move.


1389
1:3:30,303 --> 1:3:32,109
So can you tell me, Vice President Biden,


1390
1:3:32,109 --> 1:3:36,422
what was the military reason for bringing those surge troops home


1391
1:3:36,422 --> 1:3:36,922
before the fighting season ended?


1392
1:3:36,922 --> 1:3:38,43
[Biden] The military reason was bringing


1393
1:3:38,43 --> 1:3:40,503
— by the way, when the president announced the surge —


1394
1:3:40,503 --> 1:3:41,972
you'll remember, Martha —


1395
1:3:41,972 --> 1:3:46,815
he said, the surge will be out by the end of the summer.


1396
1:3:46,815 --> 1:3:49,908
The military said, the surge will be out.


1397
1:3:49,908 --> 1:3:51,316
Nothing political about this.


1398
1:3:51,316 --> 1:3:53,769
Before the surge occurred


1399
1:3:53,769 --> 1:3:55,838
— so you be a little straight with me here, too —


1400
1:3:55,838 --> 1:3:58,624
before the surge occurred, we said,


1401
1:3:58,624 --> 1:4:1,177
they'll be out by the end of the summer.


1402
1:4:1,177 --> 1:4:3,794
That's what the military said. The reason for that is —


1403
1:4:3,794 --> 1:4:5,477
[Raddatz] Military follows orders.


1404
1:4:5,477 --> 1:4:7,432
They — I mean, there — trust me, there are people —


1405
1:4:7,432 --> 1:4:8,55
[Biden] Sure —


1406
1:4:8,55 --> 1:4:9,794
[Raddatz] — who were concerned about pulling out on the fighting season.


1407
1:4:9,794 --> 1:4:11,614
[Biden] But — there are people that were concerned,


1408
1:4:11,614 --> 1:4:12,899
but not the Joint Chiefs.


1409
1:4:12,899 --> 1:4:16,9
That was their recommendation in the Oval Office


1410
1:4:16,9 --> 1:4:18,926
to the president of the United States of America.


1411
1:4:18,926 --> 1:4:20,72
I sat there.


1412
1:4:20,72 --> 1:4:22,995
I'm sure you'll find someone who disagrees with the Pentagon.


1413
1:4:22,995 --> 1:4:27,132
I'm positive you'll find that within the military. But that's not the case here.


1414
1:4:27,132 --> 1:4:30,22
And secondly, the reason why the military said that


1415
1:4:30,22 --> 1:4:34,457
is you cannot wait and have a cliff.


1416
1:4:34,457 --> 1:4:39,852
It takes, you know, months and months and months to draw down forces.


1417
1:4:39,852 --> 1:4:40,491
(Inaudible) — cannot wait —


1418
1:4:40,491 --> 1:4:41,329
[Ryan] Let me bring some


1419
1:4:41,329 --> 1:4:44,368
— let me try and illustrate the issue here, because I think this —


1420
1:4:44,368 --> 1:4:45,668
it can get a little confusing.


1421
1:4:45,668 --> 1:4:49,114
We've all met with General Allen and General Scaparotti in Afghanistan


1422
1:4:49,114 --> 1:4:51,152
to talk about fighting seasons.


1423
1:4:51,152 --> 1:4:52,283
Here's the way it works.


1424
1:4:52,283 --> 1:4:54,321
The mountain passes fill in with snow.


1425
1:4:54,321 --> 1:4:58,555
The Taliban and the terrorists and the Haqqani and the Quetta shura


1426
1:4:58,555 --> 1:5:2,178
come over from Pakistan to fight our men and women.


1427
1:5:2,178 --> 1:5:3,75
When it fills in with snow, they can't do it.


1428
1:5:3,75 --> 1:5:5,219
That's what we call fighting seasons.


1429
1:5:5,219 --> 1:5:7,953
In the warm months fighting gets really high;


1430
1:5:7,953 --> 1:5:9,853
in the winter it goes down.


1431
1:5:9,853 --> 1:5:15,597
And so when Admiral Mullen and General Petraeus came to Congress and said,


1432
1:5:15,597 --> 1:5:19,293
if you pull these people out before the fighting season is end,


1433
1:5:19,293 --> 1:5:22,144
it puts people more at risk — that's the problem.


1434
1:5:22,144 --> 1:5:25,397
Yes, we drew 22,000 troops down last month.


1435
1:5:25,397 --> 1:5:27,833
But the remaining troops that are there,


1436
1:5:27,833 --> 1:5:31,364
who still have the same mission to prosecute, counterinsurgency,


1437
1:5:31,364 --> 1:5:34,208
are doing it with fewer people.


1438
1:5:34,208 --> 1:5:35,139
That makes them less safe.


1439
1:5:35,139 --> 1:5:35,639
[Biden] (Inaudible.)


1440
1:5:35,639 --> 1:5:40,13
[Ryan] We're sending fewer people out in all these hot spots


1441
1:5:40,13 --> 1:5:42,53
to do the same job that they were supposed to do a month ago —


1442
1:5:42,53 --> 1:5:43,769
[Biden] Because we turned it over —


1443
1:5:43,769 --> 1:5:45,365
[Ryan] — but we took 22,000 people out for them to do it.


1444
1:5:45,365 --> 1:5:48,956
[Biden] — we turned it over to the Afghan troops we trained.


1445
1:5:48,956 --> 1:5:55,31
No one got pulled out that didn't get filled in by trained Afghan personnel.


1446
1:5:55,31 --> 1:5:59,207
And he's — he's — he's conflating 2 issues.


1447
1:5:59,207 --> 1:6:2,537
The fighting season that Petraeus was talking about


1448
1:6:2,537 --> 1:6:7,259
and former — and Admiral Mullen was the fighting season this spring.


1449
1:6:7,259 --> 1:6:11,439
That's what he was talking about. We did not — we did not pull them out.


1450
1:6:11,439 --> 1:6:13,693
[Ryan] The calendar works the same every year. (Chuckles.)


1451
1:6:13,693 --> 1:6:15,459
[Biden] It does work the same every year. (Inaudible) — there —


1452
1:6:15,459 --> 1:6:18,405
[Ryan] (Chuckles.) Spring, summer, fall — (chuckles) —


1453
1:6:18,405 --> 1:6:20,259
it's warm or it's not.


1454
1:6:20,259 --> 1:6:23,68
They're still fighting us, they're still coming over the passes,


1455
1:6:23,68 --> 1:6:27,139
they'll — they're still coming in to Zabul or to Kunar,


1456
1:6:27,139 --> 1:6:28,163
to all of these areas,


1457
1:6:28,163 --> 1:6:30,924
but we are sending fewer people to the front to fight them.


1458
1:6:30,924 --> 1:6:31,516
And that is not safe.


1459
1:6:31,516 --> 1:6:34,849
[Biden] That's right, because that's the Afghan responsibility.


1460
1:6:34,849 --> 1:6:35,857
We've trained them.


1461
1:6:35,857 --> 1:6:36,941
[Ryan] Not in the East.


1462
1:6:36,941 --> 1:6:38,801
[Raddatz] Let's move — let's move to another war.


1463
1:6:38,801 --> 1:6:39,901
[Biden] Not in the East? (Inaudible) —


1464
1:6:39,901 --> 1:6:41,168
[Ryan] (Inaudible) — East, RC-East —


1465
1:6:41,168 --> 1:6:42,68
[Biden] RC-East, most dangerous place in the world.


1466
1:6:42,68 --> 1:6:44,903
[Ryan] That's why — that's why we don't want to send fewer people to do the job.


1467
1:6:44,903 --> 1:6:46,601
[Biden] That's — that's why we should send Americans in to do the job


1468
1:6:46,601 --> 1:6:50,298
instead of the — you'd rather Americans be going in and doing the job


1469
1:6:50,298 --> 1:6:50,798
instead of — (inaudible) —


1470
1:6:50,798 --> 1:6:51,806
[Ryan] No. We are already sending Americans to do the job —


1471
1:6:51,806 --> 1:6:52,306
[Biden] No —


1472
1:6:52,306 --> 1:6:53,652
[Ryan] — but fewer of them. That's the whole point.


1473
1:6:53,652 --> 1:6:54,214
[Biden] That — that's right.


1474
1:6:54,214 --> 1:6:59,683
We're sending in more Afghans to do the job, Afghans to do the job.


1475
1:6:59,683 --> 1:7:2,957
[Raddatz] Let's move to another war, the civil war in Syria,


1476
1:7:2,957 --> 1:7:5,611
where there are estimates that — estimates


1477
1:7:5,611 --> 1:7:9,826
that more than 25,000, 30,000 people have now been killed.


1478
1:7:9,826 --> 1:7:13,532
In March of last year, President Obama explained the military action


1479
1:7:13,532 --> 1:7:18,4
taken in Libya by saying it was in the national interest to go in


1480
1:7:18,4 --> 1:7:21,682
and prevent further massacres from occurring there.


1481
1:7:21,682 --> 1:7:25,72
So why doesn't the same logic apply in Syria? Vice President Biden.


1482
1:7:25,72 --> 1:7:28,389
[Biden] It's a different country. It's a different country.


1483
1:7:28,389 --> 1:7:31,716
It is 5 times as large geographically.


1484
1:7:31,716 --> 1:7:35,776
It has 1/5 the population that is Libya,


1485
1:7:35,776 --> 1:7:38,72
1/5 the population, 5 times as large geographically.


1486
1:7:38,72 --> 1:7:41,996
It's in a part of the world where you're not going to see


1487
1:7:41,996 --> 1:7:44,201
whatever would come from that war.


1488
1:7:44,201 --> 1:7:47,317
It'd seep into a regional war.


1489
1:7:47,317 --> 1:7:50,598
You're in a country that is heavily populated


1490
1:7:50,598 --> 1:7:53,63
in the midst of the most dangerous area in the world.


1491
1:7:53,63 --> 1:7:58,63
And in fact, if, in fact, it blows up and the wrong people gain control,


1492
1:7:58,63 --> 1:8:1,57
it's going to have impact on the entire region,


1493
1:8:1,57 --> 1:8:3,865
causing potentially regional wars.


1494
1:8:3,865 --> 1:8:6,822
We are working hand in glove with the Turks,


1495
1:8:6,822 --> 1:8:8,645
with the Jordanians, with the Saudis


1496
1:8:8,645 --> 1:8:11,585
and with all the people in the region


1497
1:8:11,585 --> 1:8:15,275
attempting to identify the people who deserve the help


1498
1:8:15,275 --> 1:8:18,56
so that when Assad goes and he will go,


1499
1:8:18,56 --> 1:8:21,274
there will be a legitimate government that follows on,


1500
1:8:21,274 --> 1:8:24,473
not an al-Qaida-sponsored government that follows on.


1501
1:8:24,473 --> 1:8:28,387
And all this loose talk of my friend, Governor Romney,


1502
1:8:28,387 --> 1:8:30,959
and the congressman about how we're going to do,


1503
1:8:30,959 --> 1:8:32,607
we could do so much more in there,


1504
1:8:32,607 --> 1:8:37,207
what more would they do other than put American boots on the ground?


1505
1:8:37,207 --> 1:8:41,895
The last thing America needs is to get into another ground war


1506
1:8:41,895 --> 1:8:45,191
in the Middle East requiring tens of thousands


1507
1:8:45,191 --> 1:8:48,613
if not well over a hundred thousand American forces.


1508
1:8:48,613 --> 1:8:52,598
That — they are the facts. They are the facts.


1509
1:8:52,598 --> 1:8:55,381
Now, every time the governor is asked about this,


1510
1:8:55,381 --> 1:8:56,466
he doesn't say any — he say —


1511
1:8:56,466 --> 1:9:1,172
he goes up with a whole lot of verbiage,


1512
1:9:1,172 --> 1:9:2,318
but when he gets pressed,


1513
1:9:2,318 --> 1:9:6,693
he says, no, he would not do anything different than we are doing now.


1514
1:9:6,693 --> 1:9:9,28
Are they proposing putting American troops on the ground,


1515
1:9:9,28 --> 1:9:11,781
putting American aircraft in their airspace?


1516
1:9:11,781 --> 1:9:12,65
Is that what they're proposing?


1517
1:9:12,65 --> 1:9:15,11
If they do, they should speak up and say so.


1518
1:9:15,11 --> 1:9:18,163
But that's not what they're saying.


1519
1:9:18,163 --> 1:9:25,354
We are doing it exactly like we need to do to identify those forces


1520
1:9:25,354 --> 1:9:28,176
who, in fact, will provide for a stable government


1521
1:9:28,176 --> 1:9:32,691
and not cause a regional Sunni-Shia war when Bassad (ph)


1522
1:9:32,691 --> 1:9:34,543
— when Bashir Assad falls.


1523
1:9:34,543 --> 1:9:35,997
[Raddatz] Congressman Ryan.


1524
1:9:35,997 --> 1:9:40,813
[Ryan] Nobody is proposing to send troops to Syria — American troops.


1525
1:9:40,813 --> 1:9:42,652
Now let me say it this way.


1526
1:9:42,652 --> 1:9:44,934
How would we do things differently?


1527
1:9:44,934 --> 1:9:48,469
We wouldn't refer Bashar Assad as a reformer


1528
1:9:48,469 --> 1:9:52,92
when he's killing his own civilians with his Russian-provided weapons.


1529
1:9:52,92 --> 1:9:56,639
We wouldn't be outsourcing our foreign policy to the United Nations,


1530
1:9:56,639 --> 1:10:0,816
giving Vladimir Putin veto power over our efforts


1531
1:10:0,816 --> 1:10:2,624
to try and deal with this issue.


1532
1:10:2,624 --> 1:10:4,37
He's vetoed 3 of them.


1533
1:10:4,37 --> 1:10:8,2
Hillary Clinton went to Russia to try and convince him not to do so;


1534
1:10:8,2 --> 1:10:9,736
they thwarted her efforts.


1535
1:10:9,736 --> 1:10:11,36
She said they were on the wrong side of history.


1536
1:10:11,36 --> 1:10:12,182
She was right about that.


1537
1:10:12,182 --> 1:10:15,879
This is just one more example of how the Russia reset's not working.


1538
1:10:15,879 --> 1:10:17,379
And so where are we?


1539
1:10:17,379 --> 1:10:19,391
After international pressure mounted,


1540
1:10:19,391 --> 1:10:22,94
then President Obama said Bashar Assad should go.


1541
1:10:22,94 --> 1:10:23,624
It's been over a year.


1542
1:10:23,624 --> 1:10:27,639
The man has slaughtered tens of thousands of his own people


1543
1:10:27,639 --> 1:10:30,62
and more foreign fighters are spilling into this country.


1544
1:10:30,62 --> 1:10:35,698
So the longer this has gone on, the more people


1545
1:10:35,698 --> 1:10:37,9
— groups like al-Qaida are going in.


1546
1:10:37,9 --> 1:10:41,526
We could have more easily identified the Free Syrian Army,


1547
1:10:41,526 --> 1:10:44,234
the freedom fighters, working with our allies,


1548
1:10:44,234 --> 1:10:46,585
the Turks, the Qataris, the Saudis,


1549
1:10:46,585 --> 1:10:51,642
had we had a better plan in place to begin with, working through our allies.


1550
1:10:51,642 --> 1:10:54,326
But no, we waited for Kofi Annan


1551
1:10:54,326 --> 1:10:57,85
to try and come up with an agreement through the U.N.


1552
1:10:57,85 --> 1:10:59,439
That bought Bashar Assad time.


1553
1:10:59,439 --> 1:11:3,316
We gave Russia veto power over our efforts through the U.N.


1554
1:11:3,316 --> 1:11:7,403
and meanwhile about 30,000 Syrians are dead.


1555
1:11:7,403 --> 1:11:10,645
[Biden] What would my friend do differently?


1556
1:11:10,645 --> 1:11:12,525
If you notice, he never answers the question.


1557
1:11:12,525 --> 1:11:14,435
[Ryan] No, I would — I — we would not be going through the U.N.


1558
1:11:14,435 --> 1:11:15,397
on all of these things —


1559
1:11:15,397 --> 1:11:18,47
[Biden] Let — let — let me — you don't go through the U.N.


1560
1:11:18,47 --> 1:11:22,234
We are in the process now and have been for months


1561
1:11:22,234 --> 1:11:25,491
in making sure that help, humanitarian aid,


1562
1:11:25,491 --> 1:11:27,685
as well as other aid and training,


1563
1:11:27,685 --> 1:11:31,156
is getting to those forces that we believe,


1564
1:11:31,156 --> 1:11:35,103
the Turks believe, the Jordanians believe, the Saudis believe


1565
1:11:35,103 --> 1:11:38,289
are the free forces inside of Syria.


1566
1:11:38,289 --> 1:11:39,897
That is under way.


1567
1:11:39,897 --> 1:11:46,28
Our allies were all on the same page, NATO as well as our Arab allies,


1568
1:11:46,28 --> 1:11:49,601
in terms of trying to get a settlement.


1569
1:11:49,601 --> 1:11:52,855
That was their idea. We're the ones that said, enough.


1570
1:11:52,855 --> 1:11:55,737
With regard to the reset not working,


1571
1:11:55,737 --> 1:11:58,731
the fact of the matter is that Russia has a different interest in Syria


1572
1:11:58,731 --> 1:12:1,595
than we do, and that's not in our interest.


1573
1:12:1,595 --> 1:12:4,527
[Raddatz] What happens if Assad does not fall?


1574
1:12:4,527 --> 1:12:7,249
Congressman Ryan, what happens to the region?


1575
1:12:7,249 --> 1:12:9,951
What happens if he hangs on? What happens if he does?


1576
1:12:9,951 --> 1:12:14,14
[Ryan] Then Iran keeps their greatest ally in the region.


1577
1:12:14,14 --> 1:12:15,792
He's a sponsor of terrorism.


1578
1:12:15,792 --> 1:12:18,431
He'll probably continue slaughtering his people.


1579
1:12:18,431 --> 1:12:21,641
We and the world community will lose our credibility on this.


1580
1:12:21,641 --> 1:12:23,296
Look, he mentioned the reset.


1581
1:12:23,296 --> 1:12:25,119
[Raddatz] So what would Romney-Ryan do about that credibility?


1582
1:12:25,119 --> 1:12:27,768
[Ryan] Well, we agree with the same red line, actually,


1583
1:12:27,768 --> 1:12:31,344
they do on chemical weapons, but not putting American troops in,


1584
1:12:31,344 --> 1:12:32,69
other than to secure those chemical weapons.


1585
1:12:32,69 --> 1:12:35,288
They're right about that.


1586
1:12:35,288 --> 1:12:39,468
But what we should have done earlier is work with those freedom fighters,


1587
1:12:39,468 --> 1:12:41,264
those dissidents in Syria.


1588
1:12:41,264 --> 1:12:45,418
We should not have called Bashar Assad a reformer,


1589
1:12:45,418 --> 1:12:46,548
and we should not have


1590
1:12:46,548 --> 1:12:49,859
— we should not have waited to Russia to give us the green light —


1591
1:12:49,859 --> 1:12:50,774
[Biden] We didn't call Assad —


1592
1:12:50,774 --> 1:12:51,396
[Raddatz] What's your criteria for —


1593
1:12:51,396 --> 1:12:54,398
[Ryan] We should not have waited for Russia


1594
1:12:54,398 --> 1:12:55,143
to give us the green light at the U.N. to do something about it.


1595
1:12:55,143 --> 1:12:55,966
[Biden] Russia —


1596
1:12:55,966 --> 1:12:58,267
[Ryan] They're — they're still arming the man.


1597
1:12:58,267 --> 1:12:59,907
Iran is flying flights over Iraq —


1598
1:12:59,907 --> 1:13:2,454
[Biden] And the opposition is being armed —


1599
1:13:2,454 --> 1:13:5,46
[Ryan] — to help — to help — to help Bashar Assad.


1600
1:13:5,46 --> 1:13:6,289
And by the way, if we had the status of forces agreement


1601
1:13:6,289 --> 1:13:9,891
that the vice president said he would bet his vice presidency on in Iraq,


1602
1:13:9,891 --> 1:13:12,327
we probably would have been able to prevent that.


1603
1:13:12,327 --> 1:13:15,28
But he failed to achieve that as well. Again —


1604
1:13:15,28 --> 1:13:16,481
[Raddatz] Let me ask you quickly,


1605
1:13:16,481 --> 1:13:18,794
what's your criteria for intervention?


1606
1:13:18,794 --> 1:13:19,555
[Biden] I don't — yeah.


1607
1:13:19,555 --> 1:13:20,624
[Ryan] In Syria?


1608
1:13:20,624 --> 1:13:22,2
[Raddatz] Worldwide.


1609
1:13:22,2 --> 1:13:23,607
[Ryan] What is in the national interests of the American people.


1610
1:13:23,607 --> 1:13:25,26
[Raddatz] How about humanitarian interests?


1611
1:13:25,26 --> 1:13:27,83
[Ryan] What is in the national security of the American people


1612
1:13:27,83 --> 1:13:29,395
— it's got to be in the strategic national interests of our country.


1613
1:13:29,395 --> 1:13:31,938
[Raddatz] No humanitarian?


1614
1:13:31,938 --> 1:13:35,87
[Ryan] Each situation will — will come up with its own set of circumstances.


1615
1:13:35,87 --> 1:13:37,647
But putting American troops on the ground,


1616
1:13:37,647 --> 1:13:42,592
that's got to be within the national security interests of the American people.


1617
1:13:42,592 --> 1:13:45,65
[Raddatz] I want to — we're almost out of time here.


1618
1:13:45,65 --> 1:13:47,36
[Ryan] That means things like embargoes and sanctions and overflights


1619
1:13:47,36 --> 1:13:51,52
— those are things that don't put American troops on the ground.


1620
1:13:51,52 --> 1:13:53,336
But if you're talking about putting American troops on the ground,


1621
1:13:53,336 --> 1:13:56,308
only in our national security interests.


1622
1:13:56,308 --> 1:13:58,208
[Raddatz] I want to move on,


1623
1:13:58,208 --> 1:14:0,521
and I want to return home for these last few questions.


1624
1:14:0,521 --> 1:14:2,28
This debate is indeed historic.


1625
1:14:2,28 --> 1:14:8,544
We have 2 Catholic candidates, first time on a stage such as this,


1626
1:14:8,544 --> 1:14:10,615
and I would like to ask you both to tell me


1627
1:14:10,615 --> 1:14:17,27
what role your religion has played in your own personal views on abortion.


1628
1:14:17,27 --> 1:14:21,509
Please talk about how you came to that decision.


1629
1:14:21,509 --> 1:14:25,369
Talk about how your religion played a part in that.


1630
1:14:25,369 --> 1:14:28,694
And please, this is such an emotional issue for so many —


1631
1:14:28,694 --> 1:14:29,64
[Ryan] Sure.


1632
1:14:29,64 --> 1:14:31,386
[Raddatz] — people in this country.


1633
1:14:31,386 --> 1:14:37,876
Please talk personally about this if you could. Congressman Ryan.


1634
1:14:37,876 --> 1:14:40,908
[Ryan] I don't see how a person can separate their public life


1635
1:14:40,908 --> 1:14:44,103
from their private life or from their faith.


1636
1:14:44,103 --> 1:14:46,396
Our faith informs us in everything we do.


1637
1:14:46,396 --> 1:14:50,255
My faith informs me about how to take care of the vulnerable,


1638
1:14:50,255 --> 1:14:54,277
about how to make sure that people have a chance in life.


1639
1:14:54,277 --> 1:14:58,473
Now, you want to ask basically why I'm pro-life?


1640
1:14:58,473 --> 1:15:1,342
It's not simply because of my Catholic faith.


1641
1:15:1,342 --> 1:15:7,228
That's a factor, of course, but it's also because of reason and science.


1642
1:15:7,228 --> 1:15:11,482
You know, I think about 10 1/2 years ago,


1643
1:15:11,482 --> 1:15:16,493
my wife Janna and I went to Mercy Hospital in Janesville where I was born


1644
1:15:16,493 --> 1:15:20,247
for our 7-week ultrasound for our firstborn child,


1645
1:15:20,247 --> 1:15:23,202
and we saw that heartbeat.


1646
1:15:23,202 --> 1:15:27,93
Our little baby was in the shape of a bean, and to this day,


1647
1:15:27,93 --> 1:15:33,303
we have nicknamed our firstborn child, Liza, "Bean." (Chuckles.)


1648
1:15:33,303 --> 1:15:36,459
Now, I believe that life begins at conception.


1649
1:15:36,459 --> 1:15:40,522
That's why — those are the reasons why I'm pro-life.


1650
1:15:40,522 --> 1:15:42,56
Now, I understand this is a difficult issue.


1651
1:15:42,56 --> 1:15:45,954
