1666
1:16:33,314 --> 1:16:36,827
taxpayer funding in "Obamacare," taxpayer funding with foreign aid.


1667
1:16:36,827 --> 1:16:38,984
The vice-president himself went to China


1668
1:16:38,984 --> 1:16:42,926
and said that he sympathized or wouldn't second-guess


1669
1:16:42,926 --> 1:16:46,812
their 1-child policy of forced abortions and sterilizations.


1670
1:16:46,812 --> 1:16:49,378
That, to me, is pretty extreme.


1671
1:16:49,378 --> 1:16:52,289
[Raddatz] Vice President Biden.


1672
1:16:52,289 --> 1:16:56,229
[Biden] My religion defines who I am.


1673
1:16:56,229 --> 1:17:2,105
And I've been a practicing Catholic my whole life.


1674
1:17:2,105 --> 1:17:5,785
And it has particularly informed my social doctrine.


1675
1:17:5,785 --> 1:17:9,6
Catholic social doctrine talks about taking care of those who


1676
1:17:9,6 --> 1:17:15,27
— who can't take care of themselves, people who need help.


1677
1:17:15,27 --> 1:17:17,287
With regard to


1678
1:17:17,287 --> 1:17:23,957
— with regard to abortion, I accept my church's position on abortion as a


1679
1:17:23,957 --> 1:17:26,465
— what we call de fide doctrine.


1680
1:17:26,465 --> 1:17:28,782
Life begins at conception. That's the church's judgment.


1681
1:17:28,782 --> 1:17:31,846
I accept it in my personal life.


1682
1:17:31,846 --> 1:17:36,833
But I refuse to impose it on equally devout Christians and Muslims and Jews


1683
1:17:36,833 --> 1:17:39,98
and — I just refuse to impose that on others,


1684
1:17:39,98 --> 1:17:43,763
unlike my friend here, the congressman.


1685
1:17:43,763 --> 1:17:50,322
I — I do not believe that — that we have a right to tell other people


1686
1:17:50,322 --> 1:17:53,92
that women, they — they can't control their body.


1687
1:17:53,92 --> 1:17:56,864
It's a decision between them and their doctor, in my view.


1688
1:17:56,864 --> 1:17:59,876
And the Supreme Court — I'm not going to interfere with that.


1689
1:17:59,876 --> 1:18:3,396
With regard to the assault on the Catholic Church,


1690
1:18:3,396 --> 1:18:6,3
let me make it absolutely clear.


1691
1:18:6,3 --> 1:18:8,771
No religious institution, Catholic or otherwise,


1692
1:18:8,771 --> 1:18:11,672
including Catholic Social Services, Georgetown Hospital,


1693
1:18:11,672 --> 1:18:17,386
Mercy — any hospital — none has to either refer contraception.


1694
1:18:17,386 --> 1:18:20,264
None has to pay for contraception.


1695
1:18:20,264 --> 1:18:24,188
None has to be a vehicle to get contraception


1696
1:18:24,188 --> 1:18:26,422
in any insurance policy they provide.


1697
1:18:26,422 --> 1:18:29,575
That is a fact. That is a fact.


1698
1:18:29,575 --> 1:18:34,767
Now, with regard to the way in which the — we differ,


1699
1:18:34,767 --> 1:18:40,68
my friend says that he —


1700
1:18:40,68 --> 1:18:42,504
well, I guess he accepts Governor Romney's position now,


1701
1:18:42,504 --> 1:18:47,328
because in the past he has argued that there was


1702
1:18:47,328 --> 1:18:49,84
— there's rape and forcible rape.


1703
1:18:49,84 --> 1:18:52,21
He's argued that, in the case of rape or incest,


1704
1:18:52,21 --> 1:18:56,234
it was still — it would be a crime to engage in having an abortion.


1705
1:18:56,234 --> 1:19:0,288
I just fundamentally disagree with my friend.


1706
1:19:0,288 --> 1:19:1,541
[Raddatz] Congressman Ryan.


1707
1:19:1,541 --> 1:19:5,592
[Ryan] All I'm saying is if you believe that life begins at conception,


1708
1:19:5,592 --> 1:19:8,5
that therefore doesn't change the definition of life.


1709
1:19:8,5 --> 1:19:10,121
That's a principle.


1710
1:19:10,121 --> 1:19:12,96
The policy of a Romney administration is to oppose abortion


1711
1:19:12,96 --> 1:19:17,804
with exceptions for rape, incest and life of the mother.


1712
1:19:17,804 --> 1:19:22,236
Now, I've got to take issue with the Catholic Church and religious liberty.


1713
1:19:22,236 --> 1:19:26,5
[Biden] You have, on the issue of Catholic social doctrine, taken issue.


1714
1:19:26,5 --> 1:19:28,261
[Ryan] If they — if they agree with you, then why would they keep —


1715
1:19:28,261 --> 1:19:30,398
why would they keep suing you?


1716
1:19:30,398 --> 1:19:32,18
It's a distinction without a difference.


1717
1:19:32,18 --> 1:19:34,402
[Raddatz] I want to go back to the abortion question here.


1718
1:19:34,402 --> 1:19:36,275
If the Romney-Ryan ticket is elected,


1719
1:19:36,275 --> 1:19:41,85
should those who believe that abortion should remain legal be worried?


1720
1:19:41,85 --> 1:19:45,128
[Ryan] We don't think that unelected judges should make this decision;


1721
1:19:45,128 --> 1:19:48,628
that people, through their elected representatives


1722
1:19:48,628 --> 1:19:51,356
and reaching a consensus in society through the democratic process,


1723
1:19:51,356 --> 1:19:53,876
should make this determination.


1724
1:19:53,876 --> 1:19:55,237
[Biden] The court


1725
1:19:55,237 --> 1:19:58,982
— the next president will get 1 or 2 Supreme Court nominees.


1726
1:19:58,982 --> 1:20:3,93
That's how close Roe v. Wade is.


1727
1:20:3,93 --> 1:20:5,503
Just ask yourself:


1728
1:20:5,503 --> 1:20:12,23
With Robert Bork being the chief adviser on the court for — for Mr. Romney,


1729
1:20:12,23 --> 1:20:14,401
who do you think he's likely to appoint?


1730
1:20:14,401 --> 1:20:18,287
Do you think he's likely to appoint someone like Scalia


1731
1:20:18,287 --> 1:20:22,89
or someone else on the court, far right, that would outlaw Planned


1732
1:20:22,89 --> 1:20:25,95
— excuse me — outlaw abortion?


1733
1:20:25,95 --> 1:20:27,288
I suspect that would happen.


1734
1:20:27,288 --> 1:20:29,682
I guarantee you that will not happen.


1735
1:20:29,682 --> 1:20:32,429
We picked 2 people. We picked people who are open-minded.


1736
1:20:32,429 --> 1:20:34,375
They've been good justices.


1737
1:20:34,375 --> 1:20:36,305
So keep an eye on the Supreme Court —


1738
1:20:36,305 --> 1:20:37,806
[Ryan] Was there a litmus test on them?


1739
1:20:37,806 --> 1:20:39,796
[Biden] There was no litmus test.


1740
1:20:39,796 --> 1:20:43,206
We picked people who had an open mind, did not come with an agenda.


1741
1:20:43,206 --> 1:20:45,804
[Raddatz] I'm going to move on to this closing question


1742
1:20:45,804 --> 1:20:47,92
because we are running out of time.


1743
1:20:47,92 --> 1:20:50,343
It's certainly known — you've said it here tonight —


1744
1:20:50,343 --> 1:20:53,642
that the 2 of you respect our troops enormously.


1745
1:20:53,642 --> 1:20:56,703
Your son has served, and perhaps someday


1746
1:20:56,703 --> 1:20:58,953
your children will serve as well.


1747
1:20:58,953 --> 1:21:2,117
I recently spoke to a highly decorated soldier


1748
1:21:2,117 --> 1:21:6,89
who said that this presidential campaign has left him dismayed.


1749
1:21:6,89 --> 1:21:7,468
He told me, quote,


1750
1:21:7,468 --> 1:21:11,182
"The ads are so negative and they are all tearing down each other,


1751
1:21:11,182 --> 1:21:12,914
rather than building up the country."


1752
1:21:12,914 --> 1:21:16,524
What would you say to that American hero about this campaign?


1753
1:21:16,524 --> 1:21:22,835
And at the end of the day, are you ever embarrassed by the tone?


1754
1:21:22,835 --> 1:21:25,784
Vice President Biden.


1755
1:21:25,784 --> 1:21:29,136
[Biden] I would say to him the same thing I say to my son,


1756
1:21:29,136 --> 1:21:31,121
who did serve year in Iraq:


1757
1:21:31,121 --> 1:21:37,101
that we only have one truly sacred obligation as a government.


1758
1:21:37,101 --> 1:21:39,414
That's to equip those we send into harm's way


1759
1:21:39,414 --> 1:21:42,864
and care for those who come home.


1760
1:21:42,864 --> 1:21:44,9
That's the only sacred obligation we have.


1761
1:21:44,9 --> 1:21:47,914
Everything else falls behind that.


1762
1:21:47,914 --> 1:21:53,759
I would also tell him that the fact that he,


1763
1:21:53,759 --> 1:21:57,464
this decorated soldier you talked about,


1764
1:21:57,464 --> 1:22:1,59
fought for his country — that that should be honored.


1765
1:22:1,59 --> 1:22:3,665
He should not be thrown into a category


1766
1:22:3,665 --> 1:22:8,305
of the 47% who don't pay their taxes while he was out there fighting


1767
1:22:8,305 --> 1:22:12,354
and not having to pay taxes and somehow not taking responsibility.


1768
1:22:12,354 --> 1:22:15,668
I would also tell him that there are things


1769
1:22:15,668 --> 1:22:18,614
that have occurred in this campaign and occur in every campaign


1770
1:22:18,614 --> 1:22:22,54
that I'm sure both of us regret anyone having said,


1771
1:22:22,54 --> 1:22:27,331
particularly in these special new groups that can go out there,


1772
1:22:27,331 --> 1:22:30,141
raise all the money they want, not have to identify themselves


1773
1:22:30,141 --> 1:22:34,124
and say the most scurrilous things about the other candidate.


1774
1:22:34,124 --> 1:22:36,228
It's — it's — it's an abomination.


1775
1:22:36,228 --> 1:22:37,466
But the bottom line here is


1776
1:22:37,466 --> 1:22:41,373
I'd ask that hero you reference to take a look


1777
1:22:41,373 --> 1:22:48,371
at whether or not Governor Romney or President Obama has the conviction


1778
1:22:48,371 --> 1:22:51,458
to help lift up the middle class,


1779
1:22:51,458 --> 1:22:54,401
restore them to where they were before this Great Recession hit


1780
1:22:54,401 --> 1:22:55,595
and they got wiped out


1781
1:22:55,595 --> 1:22:58,703
or whether or not he's going to continue to focus


1782
1:22:58,703 --> 1:23:1,72
on taking care of only the very wealthy,


1783
1:23:1,72 --> 1:23:4,88
not asking them to make — pay any part of the deal


1784
1:23:4,88 --> 1:23:7,832
to bring the — bring back the middle class, the economy of this country.


1785
1:23:7,832 --> 1:23:10,219
I would ask him to take a look at


1786
1:23:10,219 --> 1:23:12,898
whether the president of the United States has acted wisely


1787
1:23:12,898 --> 1:23:15,37
in the use of force


1788
1:23:15,37 --> 1:23:18,263
and whether or not the slipshod comments being made


1789
1:23:18,263 --> 1:23:20,577
by my — my friend or by Governor Romney


1790
1:23:20,577 --> 1:23:24,915
serve — serve our interests very well.


1791
1:23:24,915 --> 1:23:28,275
But there are things that have been said in campaigns


1792
1:23:28,275 --> 1:23:32,165
that I — I find not very appealing.


1793
1:23:32,165 --> 1:23:33,33
[Raddatz] Congressman Ryan.


1794
1:23:33,33 --> 1:23:35,655
[Ryan] First of all, I'd thank him to his service to our country.


1795
1:23:35,655 --> 1:23:37,37
Second of all, I'd say,


1796
1:23:37,37 --> 1:23:39,362
we are not going to impose these devastating cuts on our military


1797
1:23:39,362 --> 1:23:42,99
which compromises their mission and their safety.


1798
1:23:42,99 --> 1:23:43,49
And then I would say,


1799
1:23:43,49 --> 1:23:47,157
you have a president who ran for president 4 years ago


1800
1:23:47,157 --> 1:23:49,15
promising hope and change


1801
1:23:49,15 --> 1:23:53,969
who has now turned his campaign into attack, blame and defame.


1802
1:23:53,969 --> 1:23:57,951
You see, if you don't have a good record to run on,


1803
1:23:57,951 --> 1:24:1,552
then you paint your opponent as someone to run from.


1804
1:24:1,552 --> 1:24:4,249
That was what President Obama said in 2008.


1805
1:24:4,249 --> 1:24:6,76
It's what he's doing right now.


1806
1:24:6,76 --> 1:24:9,285
Look at all the string of broken promises.


1807
1:24:9,285 --> 1:24:11,32
If you like your health care plan you can keep it


1808
1:24:11,32 --> 1:24:13,54
— try telling that to the 20 million people


1809
1:24:13,54 --> 1:24:15,93
who are projected to lose their health insurance


1810
1:24:15,93 --> 1:24:17,26
if "Obamacare" goes through


1811
1:24:17,26 --> 1:24:20,19
or the 7 point million — 7.4 million seniors who are going to lose it.


1812
1:24:20,19 --> 1:24:22,425
Or remember when he said this:


1813
1:24:22,425 --> 1:24:26,302
I guarantee if you make less than $250,000, your taxes won't go up.


1814
1:24:26,302 --> 1:24:30,897
Of the 21 tax increases in "Obamacare," 12 of them hit the middle class.


1815
1:24:30,897 --> 1:24:33,81
Or remember when he said, health insurance premiums will go down,


1816
1:24:33,81 --> 1:24:36,477
and $2,500 per family per year?


1817
1:24:36,477 --> 1:24:37,9
They've gone up 3,000 (dollars),


1818
1:24:37,9 --> 1:24:39,539
and they're expected to go up another 2,400 (dollars).


1819
1:24:39,539 --> 1:24:42,925
Or remember when he said, I promise by the end of my first term,


1820
1:24:42,925 --> 1:24:45,788
I'll cut the deficit in half in 4 years?


1821
1:24:45,788 --> 1:24:50,303
We've had 4 budgets, 4 trillion-dollar deficits.


1822
1:24:50,303 --> 1:24:52,746
A debt crisis is coming.


1823
1:24:52,746 --> 1:24:55,536
We can't keep spending and borrowing like this.


1824
1:24:55,536 --> 1:24:58,462
We can't just keep spending money we don't have.


1825
1:24:58,462 --> 1:25:1,728
Leaders run to problems to fix problems.


1826
1:25:1,728 --> 1:25:8,882
President Obama has not even put a credible plan on the table in any — any of his four years to deal with this debt crisis.


1827
1:25:8,882 --> 1:25:10,277
I passed 2 budgets to deal with this.


1828
1:25:10,277 --> 1:25:12,766
Mitt Romney has put 5 ideas on the table.


1829
1:25:12,766 --> 1:25:15,916
We've got to tackle this debt crisis before it tackles us.


1830
1:25:15,916 --> 1:25:19,169
The president likes to say he has a plan. He gave a speech.


1831
1:25:19,169 --> 1:25:21,67
We asked his budget office, can we see the plan?


1832
1:25:21,67 --> 1:25:23,381
They sent us to this press secretary.


1833
1:25:23,381 --> 1:25:25,488
He gave us a copy of the speech.


1834
1:25:25,488 --> 1:25:26,849
We asked the Congressional Budget Office,


1835
1:25:26,849 --> 1:25:28,894
tell us what President Obama's plan is to prevent a debt crisis.


1836
1:25:28,894 --> 1:25:31,667
They said, it's a speech; we can't estimate speeches.


1837
1:25:31,667 --> 1:25:36,275
You see? That's what we get in this administration: speeches.


1838
1:25:36,275 --> 1:25:37,72
But we're not getting leadership.


1839
1:25:37,72 --> 1:25:42,28
Mitt Romney is uniquely qualified to fix these problems.


1840
1:25:42,28 --> 1:25:46,831
His lifetime of experience, his proven track record of bipartisanship —


1841
1:25:46,831 --> 1:25:48,134
and what do we have from the president?


1842
1:25:48,134 --> 1:25:50,792
He broke his big promise to bring people together


1843
1:25:50,792 --> 1:25:52,364
to solve the country's biggest problems.


1844
1:25:52,364 --> 1:25:55,62
And what I would tell him is we don't have to settle for this.


1845
1:25:55,62 --> 1:25:56,297
[Raddatz] I — I —


1846
1:25:56,297 --> 1:25:57,66
[Ryan] We can do better than this.


1847
1:25:57,66 --> 1:25:59,252
[Biden] I hope I'll get equal time.


1848
1:25:59,252 --> 1:26:2,448
[Raddatz] I — you will get just a few minutes here, a few seconds, really.


1849
1:26:2,448 --> 1:26:7,451
[Biden] The 2 budgets the congressman introduced have eviscerated


1850
1:26:7,451 --> 1:26:10,881
all the things that the middle class cares about.


1851
1:26:10,881 --> 1:26:14,405
It has knocked 19 — it will knock 19 million people off of Medicare.


1852
1:26:14,405 --> 1:26:18,321
It will kick 200,000 children off of early education.


1853
1:26:18,321 --> 1:26:20,663
It will eliminate the tax credit people have


1854
1:26:20,663 --> 1:26:23,409
to be able to send their children to college.


1855
1:26:23,409 --> 1:26:27,622
It cuts education by $450 billion.


1856
1:26:27,622 --> 1:26:30,556
It — it — it does — it does virtually nothing,


1857
1:26:30,556 --> 1:26:35,275
except continue to increase the tax cuts for the very wealthy.


1858
1:26:35,275 --> 1:26:37,926
And, you know, we've had enough of this.


1859
1:26:37,926 --> 1:26:41,39
My — the idea that these — so concerned about these deficits,


1860
1:26:41,39 --> 1:26:45,144
I pointed out, he voted to put 2 wars on a credit card. He did —


1861
1:26:45,144 --> 1:26:47,13
[Raddatz] We're — we're going - We're going to the closing statements in a minute.


1862
1:26:47,13 --> 1:26:48,76
[Ryan] But let me — just a second —


1863
1:26:48,76 --> 1:26:50,956
[Raddatz] I — you're going to have your closing —


1864
1:26:50,956 --> 1:26:54,286
[Ryan] Not raising taxes is not cutting taxes. And by the way, our budget —


1865
1:26:54,286 --> 1:26:55,355
[Biden] We have not raised —


1866
1:26:55,355 --> 1:26:56,947
[Ryan] — we increased spending by 3% a year


1867
1:26:56,947 --> 1:26:59,134
instead of 4.5 % like they proposed.


1868
1:26:59,134 --> 1:27:3,133
[Raddatz] Let me — let me calm down things here just for a minute.


1869
1:27:3,133 --> 1:27:5,17
[Ryan] So not spending more money as much as they say is not a spending cut.


1870
1:27:5,17 --> 1:27:7,427
[Raddatz]  And I want to talk to you very briefly


1871
1:27:7,427 --> 1:27:8,834
before we go to closing statements about your own personal character.


1872
1:27:8,834 --> 1:27:13,189
If you are elected, what could you both give to this country as a man,


1873
1:27:13,189 --> 1:27:17,2
as a human being that no one else could?


1874
1:27:17,2 --> 1:27:19,565
[Ryan] Honesty. No one else could?


1875
1:27:19,565 --> 1:27:22,316
There are plenty of fine people who could lead this country.


1876
1:27:22,316 --> 1:27:24,631
But what you need are people who,


1877
1:27:24,631 --> 1:27:27,418
when they say they're going to do something, they go do it.


1878
1:27:27,418 --> 1:27:31,217
What you need are when people see problems,


1879
1:27:31,217 --> 1:27:33,717
they offer solutions to fix those problems.


1880
1:27:33,717 --> 1:27:35,155
We're not getting that.


1881
1:27:35,155 --> 1:27:37,161
Look, we can grow this economy faster.


1882
1:27:37,161 --> 1:27:39,406
That's what our 5-Point plan for a stronger middle class is all about.


1883
1:27:39,406 --> 1:27:41,472
It's about getting 12 million jobs,


1884
1:27:41,472 --> 1:27:43,202
higher take-home pay;


1885
1:27:43,202 --> 1:27:45,245
getting people out of poverty, into the middle class.


1886
1:27:45,245 --> 1:27:48,454
That means going with proven pro-growth policies that we know work


1887
1:27:48,454 --> 1:27:51,148
to get people back to work, putting ideas on the table,


1888
1:27:51,148 --> 1:27:54,666
working with Democrats — that actually works sometimes —


1889
1:27:54,666 --> 1:27:55,935
and then getting things done.


1890
1:27:55,935 --> 1:27:57,604
[Raddatz] Vice President, could we get to that


1891
1:27:57,604 --> 1:28:0,41
— to that issue of what you could bring as a man, a human being?


1892
1:28:0,41 --> 1:28:2,666
And I really am going to keep you to about 15 seconds here.


1893
1:28:2,666 --> 1:28:5,638
[Biden] Well, he gets 40, I get 15, but that's OK. That's all right.


1894
1:28:5,638 --> 1:28:7,261
[Raddatz] He didn't have 40. He didn't have 40.


1895
1:28:7,261 --> 1:28:10,592
[Biden] Now, let me tell you, I — my — my record stands for itself.


1896
1:28:10,592 --> 1:28:12,751
I never say anything I don't mean.


1897
1:28:12,751 --> 1:28:15,903
Everybody knows whatever I say, I do.


1898
1:28:15,903 --> 1:28:19,644
And my whole life has been devoted to leveling the playing field


1899
1:28:19,644 --> 1:28:22,303
for middle-class people, giving them an even break,


1900
1:28:22,303 --> 1:28:24,654
treating Main Street and Wall Street the same,


1901
1:28:24,654 --> 1:28:26,661
holding the same responsibility.


1902
1:28:26,661 --> 1:28:28,268
Look at my record.


1903
1:28:28,268 --> 1:28:30,516
It's been all about the middle class.


1904
1:28:30,516 --> 1:28:32,123
They're the people who grow this country.


1905
1:28:32,123 --> 1:28:34,183
We think you grow this country from the middle out,


1906
1:28:34,183 --> 1:28:36,273
not from the top down.


1907
1:28:36,273 --> 1:28:39,894
[Raddatz] OK. We now turn to the candidates for their closing statements.


1908
1:28:39,894 --> 1:28:41,301
Thank you, gentlemen.


1909
1:28:41,301 --> 1:28:42,985
And that coin toss, again,


1910
1:28:42,985 --> 1:28:45,274
has Vice President Biden starting with a closing statement.


1911
1:28:45,274 --> 1:28:47,369
[Biden] Well, let — let — let me say at the outset


1912
1:28:47,369 --> 1:28:51,749
that I want to thank you, Martha, for doing this, and Centre College.


1913
1:28:51,749 --> 1:28:55,544
The fact is that we're in a situation


1914
1:28:55,544 --> 1:29:0,816
where we inherited a god-awful circumstance.


1915
1:29:0,816 --> 1:29:2,716
People are in real trouble.


1916
1:29:2,716 --> 1:29:7,682
We acted to move to bring relief to the people who need the most help now.


1917
1:29:7,682 --> 1:29:13,457
And — and in the process, we 
— in case you haven't noticed, we have strong disagreements.


1918
1:29:13,457 --> 1:29:18,475
But I — you probably detected my frustration with their attitude


1919
1:29:18,475 --> 1:29:21,164
about the — the American people.


1920
1:29:21,164 --> 1:29:24,51
My friend says that 30% of the American people are takers.


1921
1:29:24,51 --> 1:29:27,931
They — Romney points out, 47%of the people


1922
1:29:27,931 --> 1:29:30,479
won't take responsibility.


1923
1:29:30,479 --> 1:29:32,271
He's talking about my mother and father.


1924
1:29:32,271 --> 1:29:34,17
And he's talking about the places I grew up in,


1925
1:29:34,17 --> 1:29:35,884
my neighbors in Scranton and Claymont.


1926
1:29:35,884 --> 1:29:37,476
He's talking about —


1927
1:29:37,476 --> 1:29:39,947
he's talking about the people that have built this country.


1928
1:29:39,947 --> 1:29:43,642
All they're looking for, Martha — all they're looking for is an even shot.


1929
1:29:43,642 --> 1:29:46,202
When they've been given the shot, they've done it.


1930
1:29:46,202 --> 1:29:47,378
They've done it.


1931
1:29:47,378 --> 1:29:49,896
Whenever you level the playing field, they've been able to move.


1932
1:29:49,896 --> 1:29:51,888
And they want a little bit of peace of mind.


1933
1:29:51,888 --> 1:29:54,386
And the president and I are not going to rest


1934
1:29:54,386 --> 1:29:57,42
until that playing field is leveled,


1935
1:29:57,42 --> 1:30:0,372
they in fact have a clear shot and they have peace of mind,


1936
1:30:0,372 --> 1:30:3,144
until they can turn to their kid and say with a degree of confidence,


1937
1:30:3,144 --> 1:30:7,357
honey, it's going to be OK. It's going to be OK.


1938
1:30:7,357 --> 1:30:11,407
That's what this is all about.


1939
1:30:11,407 --> 1:30:12,937
[Raddatz] Congressman Ryan.


1940
1:30:12,937 --> 1:30:16,225
[Ryan] I want to thank you as well, Martha, Danville, Kentucky, Centre College.


1941
1:30:16,225 --> 1:30:18,455
And I want to thank you, Joe.


1942
1:30:18,455 --> 1:30:22,184
It's been an honor to engage in this critical debate.


1943
1:30:22,184 --> 1:30:27,999
We face a very big choice. What kind of country are we going to be?


1944
1:30:27,999 --> 1:30:31,935
What kind of country are we going to give our kids?


1945
1:30:31,935 --> 1:30:34,359
President Obama — he had his chance.


1946
1:30:34,359 --> 1:30:36,109
He made his choices.


1947
1:30:36,109 --> 1:30:40,34
His economic agenda, more spending, more borrowing, higher taxes,


1948
1:30:40,34 --> 1:30:44,704
a government takeover of health care — it's not working.


1949
1:30:44,704 --> 1:30:46,755
It's failed to create the jobs we need.


1950
1:30:46,755 --> 1:30:49,751
23 million Americans are struggling for work today.


1951
1:30:49,751 --> 1:30:53,19
15% of Americans are in poverty.


1952
1:30:53,19 --> 1:30:56,182
This is not what a real recovery looks like.


1953
1:30:56,182 --> 1:31:2,649
You deserve better. Mitt Romney and I want to earn your support.


1954
1:31:2,649 --> 1:31:7,62
We're offering real reforms for a real recovery for every American.


1955
1:31:7,62 --> 1:31:12,784
Mitt Romney, his experience, his ideas, his solutions,


1956
1:31:12,784 --> 1:31:16,432
is uniquely qualified to get this job done.


1957
1:31:16,432 --> 1:31:18,717
At a time when we have a jobs crisis in America,


1958
1:31:18,717 --> 1:31:21,77
wouldn't it be nice to have a job creator in the White House?


1959
1:31:21,77 --> 1:31:23,774
The choice is clear:


1960
1:31:23,774 --> 1:31:28,85
a stagnant economy that promotes more government dependency,


1961
1:31:28,85 --> 1:31:33,548
or a dynamic, growing economy that promotes opportunity and jobs.


1962
1:31:33,548 --> 1:31:37,614
Mitt Romney and I will not duck the tough issues.


1963
1:31:37,614 --> 1:31:42,24
And we will not blame others for the next 4 years. We will take responsibility.


1964
1:31:42,24 --> 1:31:46,603
And we will not try to replace our founding principles;


1965
1:31:46,603 --> 1:31:49,49
we will reapply our founding principles.


1966
1:31:49,49 --> 1:31:53,759
The choice is clear, and the choice rests with you,


1967
1:31:53,759 --> 1:31:57,33
and we ask you for your vote. Thank you.


1968
1:31:57,33 --> 1:31:59,737
[Raddatz] And thank you both again. Thank you very much.


1969
1:31:59,737 --> 1:32:2,133
[Raddatz] This concludes the vice presidential debate.


1970
1:32:2,133 --> 1:32:6,341
Please tune in next Tuesday for the second presidential debate


1971
1:32:6,341 --> 1:32:8,9
at Hofstra University in New York.


1972
1:32:8,9 --> 1:32:10,486
I'm Martha Raddatz of ABC News.


1973
1:32:10,486 --> 1:32:13,332
I do hope all of you go to the polls. Have a good evening. (Applause.)


